title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in small amount of water for 10 minutes; drain. Add grated onion, bell pepper, beaten egg, Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushroom soup, garlic salt and salt and pepper to taste.
Grate cheese.
Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs; mix.
Butter baking dish well.
Add in layers the eggplant, cheese and crumbs, making 2 layers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Stir several times.
Add nutmeg, cinnamon and raisins.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Lay chicken in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix soup and 1/4 cup water.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over breasts and pour soup and water and 1/4 cup melted butter over stuffing.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Beat well and bake in 350° oven until it springs up when touched, around 35 to 40 minutes.

title: imperial artichoke appetizer
directions: Drain and reserve oil from 1 jar of artichokes.
Cook chopped onions in the reserved oil.
Coarsely chop artichoke hearts and add to onion mixture.
Beat the eggs and mix with onions and artichokes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bite-sized squares and serve hot.
Makes 40 appetizers.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream, dry ingredients and almond extract.
Stir.
Spread half of the batter on a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put cranberry sauce in a bowl and smash with a fork.
Spread sauce over batter.
Spread rest of batter over cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: tutti-frutti fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruits. Pour 1/4 cup of the combined syrups in a large bowl.
Add canned fruit, flaked coconut and lemon juice. Sprinkle the instant lemon pudding mix over the fruits and toss lightly to combine. Chill.
Serve in dessert dishes or sherbets. Top with Cool Whip and a cherry.

title: deviled eggs with ham
directions: Put
yolks
in
bowl.
Mix mashed eggs with mayonnaise, mustard and pepper.
Fold in capers and ham, reserving about 2 teaspoons of the ham for garnish.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix and bake in same 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt butter and chocolate in pan.
Add sugar and mix.
Add 2 eggs and mix.
Add 3/4 cup flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Melt margarine.
Add it to sugar, salt, eggs and the dissolved yeast.
Then add flour, about 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Put into greased bowl.
Cover and let stand in fridge overnight or even 3 to 4 days.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll to about 3/8 inch. Cut each circle into 16 pie-shaped wedges.
Roll each piece, starting at wide end.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: egg and cheese puff
directions: Make all measurements level.
Beat eggs and combine with onion, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese which has been cut into 1/4-inch cubes.
Heat shortening in frying pan.
Dip as much mixture as large spoon will hold and drop into hot shortening.
Fry golden brown on both sides.
Can be used as main coarse and especially delicious served with Sauteed Tomatoes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Read through directions first.
Add ingredients in order listed.
Be sure cinnamon, salt and sugar are sifted together. Add flour last. Dice the apples and chop the nuts.
Allow the raisins and nuts to soak in oil for a few minutes to prevent burning.
This cake is best about the second or third day.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: harvey wallbanger pudding cake
directions: Mix ingredients together as for a cake.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: far east salad
directions: Wash and dry greens.
Combine in a bowl with drained water chestnuts, drained oranges, onions and pea pods.
Combine Soy sauce, vinegar, oil, sugar, and ginger in a jar with a lid.
Shake well.
Pour over salad and toss.
Stir in noodles just before serving.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt in saucepan.
Bring to full boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and walnuts.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Yields 2 1/4 pounds.

title: chili beans
directions: Wash and sort beans.
Place beans, ham hock, garlic, salt and pepper into a pot with 8 cups of water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in order in a casserole bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: huntington chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In small saucepan, over low heat, melt together chocolate and shortening. Remove from heat, let cool slightly and stir in vanilla.
In a small bowl, combine flour and sugar; mix well.
Add flour-sugar mixture and milk to chocolate mixture alternately.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; mixing until well combined.
Spread in pan and bake for about 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: jalapeno-corn quiche
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pastry with fork.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes; remove from oven and gently prick.
Bake 5 minutes more, cool.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Saute onion and combine with remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into pastry shell and sprinkle with bacon.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: easy, no egg, one pan chocolate cake
directions: In an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, sift and mix together dry ingredients.
Make three wells in the flour mixture.
Put the vanilla in the first, vinegar in the second and the margarine in the third.
Pour water over all.
Mix until all ingredients are entirely moistened.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. Also, makes 2 layers.

title: telegram ham
directions: Spray the inside of the frying pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Put ham slices in the frying pan.
Over medium heat, brown both sides of the ham slices.

title: chicken and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion and pepper; pour off fat.
Add soups, chicken, rice and water.
Simmer about 20 minutes, until the rice is soft.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Great for office luncheons!!!

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture and bake in moderately hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Beat all ingredients together except shrimp.
Add shrimp and mix.
Refrigerate.
Spread on crackers of choice.

title: carrot salad
directions: Boil carrots in salted water just until tender; drain and place in 2-quart covered casserole.
Combine tomato sauce, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce; mix well.
Pour over carrots.
Add onion, green pepper, corn and celery.
Cover and marinate overnight.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: fettuccine vegetini
directions: In medium skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Add broccoli, pepper and carrot; saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine water, bouillon, teriyaki sauce, sherry and ginger.
Stir into skillet; heat 1 minute.
Toss with fettuccine.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's cheese ball
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together thoroughly the butter, shortening, eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: grandma's old-fashioned oatmeal
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt.
Stirring constantly, add oatmeal, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook 1 minute.
Add milk and reheat to boiling state.
Pour into serving dish and top with butter and brown sugar. Serves 6.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine the oleo, powdered sugar and flour and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: Saute hamburg.
Place in 4-quart kettle.
Add 3 quarts water. Cook meat until tender.
Add potatoes, green beans, tomatoes, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking for about 1 hour. Sometimes more liquid needs to be added and other vegetables may be added such as peas and 1/4 cup rice.
Also a soup bone can be used instead of hamburg.

title: banana applesauce bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: no-yuck brussels sprouts
directions: Blanch Brussels sprouts in boiling water.
Drain and cut Brussels sprouts in half.
Dredge sprouts in flour, salt and pepper.
Coat floured sprouts with beaten egg.
Roll egg covered sprouts in bread crumbs.
Heat 3 tablespoons olive oil in skillet. Add minced garlic.
Pan-fry sprouts in garlic and oil until browned.
Drain on paper towel and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Bring juice from the can of pineapple to a boil.
Mix sugar, eggs, lemon juice and add to the pineapple juice.
Simmer until thick and cool overnight.
Add 8 ounces Cool Whip to mixture the next day, then add fruit and marshmallows.
Serves 15.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, but sugar.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Mix well again before serving.
Serves 8.

title: beefy tomato pasta sauce
directions: Cook ground beef in a large skillet, stirring until browned and crumbly. Place in a colander. Pour hot water over ground beef and drain well. Wipe skillet with a paper towel to remove any remaining drippings. Return ground beef to skillet.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix thoroughly and put in jar with tight lid.
Use 2 level teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: pennsylvania dutch potato salad
directions: Scrub and cook potatoes in their jackets.
When tender, peel and dice.
Add the celery, hard-cooked eggs and onion; toss lightly.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp and brown.
To the beaten eggs, add sugar, salt, pepper, mustard and a mixture of vinegar and water; mix well.
Pour egg mixture into hot bacon and fat and stir until mixture thickens (about 10 minutes).
Pour over the potato mixture and toss lightly to mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours before serving.
Garnish with minced parsley.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: low calorie trifle
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Top 1/2 cup of water, add ice cubes to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to jello and let begin to jell. Slice banana and roll in lemon juice.
Place cubed angel food cake in bowl and dribble orange juice over it.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of wax paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using mallet or rolling pin.
Set aside.
Combine honey and mustard; spread on both sides of chicken, then dredge chicken in chopped pecans.
Arrange chicken in a lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for 9-inch 2-crust pie. Roll 2/3 of the pastry for bottom crust.
Fit into 9-inch pie pan. Roll remainder into rectangle, about 10 x 6-inches.
Cut into 12 strips, each 1/2-inch wide.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 3/4 cup granulated sugar. Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place half the biscuits in greased Bundt/tube pan. Sprinkle half the pecans.
Repeat.
Pour rest of mixture
and remaining ingredients in saucepan. Bring to hard boil and pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let it cool for 2 to 5 minutes and turn onto serving dish. Can be sliced or picked apart with fingers.
Yummy!

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except for food coloring.
Mix ingredients until smooth, then add food coloring.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in 3 or 4 round pans.
Fill pans half full.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Put lettuce in bottom of bowl; add cut up onions and tops. Add peas, then eggs.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise and put on top.
Cover with bacon bits.

title: asparagus souffle
directions: Put asparagus, eggs, mushroom soup, cheese and mayonnaise in blender; blend until well mixed.
Pour into greased, shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; slice thin.
Chop onions and peppers.
Combine with cucumbers and salt; let stand 3 hours, then drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in pot.
Bring to boil.
Add drained cucumbers; heat thoroughly (do not boil).
Pack while hot in hot jars; seal at once.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Heat cornstarch, sugar and water to boiling.
Stir in jello. Add strawberries.
Pour in baked deep shell pie crust.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Chill the mixture until it becomes firm.
Shape into two balls and roll each in the crushed pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat pudding mix, sugar, milk and egg yolks in saucepan until it	is
thick.
Remove
from heat and beat until smooth. Add coconut,
vanilla
and margarine.
Put in baked pie shell. Add meringue and sprinkle with coconut on top.

title: mint brownies
directions: Cream the sugar with the margarine. Add the eggs, beating after each egg. Stir in the syrup.
Mix in the flour and baking powder.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Refrigerate 20 minutes or until cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to soft boil.	Slow cook or it will get grainy.
When
it
reaches
soft
ball,
add
butter, vanilla and 3 oversized heaping ladles of peanut butter.
Stir until blended smooth, then set pan in cold water to thicken to just about pouring stage.
Put
in
whatever
you want and let cool.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vegetable oil and vinegar thoroughly and sugar is completely dissolved.
Pour over sauerkraut, pepper, celery and pimentos; mix.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Can be stored in a jar in the refrigerator for approximately 1 month.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and jello together.
Add remaining ingredients to it.
Mix and bake in a large sheet pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesecake dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until well blended and smooth. Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Serve with assorted fruits, cookies or cake cubes.
Makes 2 cups.
Contains approximately 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: kolaches
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
a
little of the milk (minus the 2 cups) 5
minutes, long enough to dissolve.
In large bowl mix all ingredients.
Mix
by
hand
until smooth (I use a wooden dough spoon).
Let rise about 5 minutes, then stir again.
Let rise again, about 20 minutes.

title: holiday cranberry punch
directions: Heat 1 pint of cranberry juice and stir in jelly; dissolve. Add orange juice; blend.
Chill.
Pour into punch bowl and add remaining ingredients.

title: sugar free fudge
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate in saucepan.
Stir in equal and vanilla.
Combine chocolate mixture with softened cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts and spread mixture in lightly greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares.

title: grandma's slaw
directions: In a large bowl, put layers of cabbage and onions.
Pour sugar over the top.
Then mix the rest of ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over slaw.
Serves 10.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix together and serve with seafood.

title: meatball sauce
directions: Make meatballs and bake in oven until done.
In saucepan, mix grape jelly and chili sauce until mixed together.
Add meatballs to sauce and heat.
Keep warm when serving.

title: stove top garlic potatoes
directions: Cut stems and lower bottom leaves from artichoke.
Cut approximately 1 1/2 inches from top leaves.
Soak in cold, salted water for about 30 minutes; drain on paper towels.
Stuff each leaf with stuffing.
Steam in large pot or roasting pan.
Pour 1 tablespoon olive oil on top of stuffed artichoke before steaming.

title: deviled beets
directions: Blend butter, mustard, honey, worcestershire sauce, paprika, heat and pour over warm beets.

title: saturday chicken
directions: Take the chicken and garlic salt and salt it a bit, then paprika it thoroughly.
Next, spread it out in one layer in a shallow baking pan.
Dilute the soup with the cream, pour it over the chicken and sprinkle with parsley on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: basic cookie mix
directions: In a 6-quart or larger bowl, cream shortening and sugar with electric mixer, adding sugar to the shortening gradually.
Blend thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture slowly, using low speed.
Mix until like coarse corn meal.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: ham and cheese nibbles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix biscuit mix, cheese and ham.
Stir and blend well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter together until crumbly, much like pie crust.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool a little.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over first mixture and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool a little and cut into bars.

title: annie's crabmeat cocktail spread
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: spinach in sauce
directions: Clean spinach of stems and wash.
Cook in water with some salt for about 20 minutes.
Pour through colander and chop.
Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add flour and brown for about 1 minute.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil, drain and cool squash.
Mix in carrot, pimento and sour cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Place 1/2 of mixture on bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Add squash mixture, top with rest of stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: bacon dip
directions: Fry bacon extra crisp and drain.
Mix cheeses together. Crumble bacon and combine with cheese.
Chill.
Serve with bagels or crackers.

title: classic coconut cake(1992 wv state fair blue ribbon winner)
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in flavorings.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold into creamed mixture.

title: spanish eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and
cut	in thin slices.
Cook in salted boiling water
(with onion) until transparent.
Drain well and beat slightly with fork.
Mix eggs, crackers, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup cheese	together.
Add	eggplant
and put in well-buttered casserole.	Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mango chutney
directions: Heat all ingredients in a saucepan to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered until slightly thickened, about 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter on stove.
Mix yolks, milk, flour and salt well with blender.
Pour yolks, milk, flour and salt mixture into melted sugar and butter and cook over low heat until thick; stir often.
Pour into two 9-inch cooled baked pie crusts. Top with your favorite meringue recipe.

title: coffee cake
directions: Prepare a 9 x 13-inch pan and preheat
oven to 375°.

title: chicken purlo
directions: Boil and debone chicken; put into casserole dish.
Add rice, onion soup, chicken broth and butter.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: cheesy mexican cornbread squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef in skillet over medium- high heat, drain.
Stir in onion, green pepper, 16 ounce jar salsa, corn and spices.
Reduce heat to low.
Continue cooking 15 minutes. Set aside.
Make cornmeal mix according to can directions.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Spread meat mixture evenly over cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese and olives.
Continue baking 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with sour cream and salsa.
Serves 8.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix well and pour over crackers. Stir until crackers look dull.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic until clear. Add meat and cook until all red is cooked and it is white.
Sift flour over meat and add chili powder, salt and pepper, if desired. Add tomato sauce and water to taste.
Bring to a good boil.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dixie crumb cake
directions: Crumb together sugar, shortening, and flour.
Add cinnamon and cloves.
Save 1 cup for topping.

title: cheese ring
directions: Grate cheese, then mix it with mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Add chopped onion and pecans.
Stir well.
Add pepper to taste.
Spoon into mold sprayed with Pam.
Remove from mold and top with preserves.
Serve with crackers.

title: green bean and sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cheese, sausage and beans and place into shell.
Beat eggs with milk and salt and pour over pie. Sprinkle with onions (optional mushrooms and parsley).
Bake for 1 hour.

title: veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight so flavors blend.

title: classic chicken risotto
directions: Heat butter and oil in a large saucepan.
Saute the onion and chicken for 3 minutes.
Add rice and Italian seasoning; cook for 2 minutes.
Add Herb-Ox bouillon cubes, water and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Stir once and lower heat to simmer.
Cover and cook for 18 minutes, until rice is creamy and liquid is absorbed.
Remove bay leaf.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cecilian meat roll
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Add hamburger; mix well. Flatten hamburger into 13 x 9 x 2 casserole dish.
Layer ham on top of the hamburger.
Sprinkle cheese over ham.
Roll both ends to form a log and seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and garnish with crisp cooked bacon bits.

title: quick strawberry pineapple dessert
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O and mold in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan. While Jell-O is setting, mix pineapple pudding and chill.
Just before serving, assemble dessert.
Cut Jell-O into 8 squares the size of graham cracker squares.
On a dessert plate place a graham cracker, then a square of Jell-O, then put pineapple pudding on Jell-O and then add another graham cracker square.
Add a dollop of Cool Whip and sprinkle lightly with ginger.
Each serving is made separately.
Serves 8.

title: cherry-sherry jubilee
directions: Drain the syrup from the canned cherries and add water to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Heat the liquid to a simmer; add the jello and stir to dissolve.
Add sherry.
Add the drained cherries and almonds.
As with additions to all gelatin mixtures, solids will distribute better if you can wait until the gelatin is partially set.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Season chops to taste and brown in small amount of fat on both sides.
Place in baking dish just large enough to hold your chops. On top of each chop, place a slice of onion, green pepper and 1 tablespoon of rice.
Mix beef consomme and water.
Pour over all. Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix salt, celery seed, vinegar and sugar.
Pour this mixture over sliced vegetables and place in covered dish in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Best is made day before or at least several hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding flour and oats last. Drop by teaspoon on very lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Boil the chicken in water until completely done.
Salt to taste.
When done, remove chicken from broth.
Make biscuit dough. Roll out dough as thin as possible; cut dough into strips about 1-inch wide.
While the broth boils rapidly, break off the strips in pieces about 2-inches long and put into broth.
Pepper to taste.
Take the meat off the bones and put parts of the meat into the dumplings.
If necessary, add some butter for richness.
Do not let the dumplings get too dry.
Add broth.

title: amish sugar pie
directions: In unbaked pie shell, mix brown sugar, flour and salt.
Pour milk over this mixture but do not mix together.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: healthy potato-leek soup
directions: In a heavy pot, saute leeks and celery.
Add potatoes, water or stock, and bay leaf; cook until tender.
Let cool briefly. Then, while stirring with a whisk or blending, add dry milk and margarine.
Garnish with parsley, chives, scallion or dill, if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: turkey and cornbread dressing
directions: Combine cornbread with broth; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: date balls
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add butter, milk and dates.
Cook on low heat until melted and mixture leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies, nuts and coconut.
When cool to handle, shape into balls and roll in coconut, if desired.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process.
Pour into glasses and garnish each drink with an additional strawberry, if available.

title: blackberry apple jelly
directions: In a large kettle, combine the blackberries and water; simmer for 5 minutes.
Strain through a jelly bag, reserving juice, discarding pulp.
Remove and discard stems (do not pare or core). Cut into small pieces, place in the kettle.
Add just enough water to cover; simmer until apples are soft (20 minutes).
Strain through jelly bag, reserving juice and discarding pulp.
Measure the reserved juices and put in kettle.
Add water and apple juice to make 4 cups.
Stir in lemon juice and sugar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add pectin, stirring until mixture boils (1 minute).
Remove from heat; take off foam.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Process for 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 9 1/2 pints.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Put rest of cake batter on top of cinnamon mixture.
Marble by running knife through.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: *Mozzarella, Cheddar, etc.; 3 kinds work well.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine sugar, half and half and salt in deep 3-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Stir in butter.
Microwave at High for 7 to 9 1/2 minutes or until mixture reaches soft-ball stage (235°), stirring once.
Stir in pecans and cool about 1 minute.
Beat by hand until mixture is creamy and begins to thicken (about 3 minutes).
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in peanuts gradually so as not to lose the boil.
Keep at a rolling boil until peanuts pop and turn brown.
Remove from heat; add soda, stirring well.
Add salt.
Pour on a well-greased platter. Allow room for candy to spread.
When cold, break in clumps. Yield:
20 to 25 servings.

title: raspberry yogurt and fruit
directions: Puree raspberries with syrup in food processor or blender. Strain; discard seeds.
In a small saucepan over high heat, bring raspberry puree to boiling.
In a small bowl, combine cold water and cornstarch; add to boiling puree.
Cook over medium-high heat, whisking constantly, 2 to 4 minutes, or until slightly thickened. Transfer to mixing bowl.
Put in freezer for 15 minutes, or until cold, but not frozen.

title: borsch(with beef)
directions: Trim all fat from beef; place beef and bone in deep pot.
Add water, bouillon cubes, salt and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; skim. Cover and simmer 1 hour until beef is almost tender.
Remove beef, bone and bay leaf.
Cut beef into bite pieces, return to simmering stock.
Stir in tomato paste.
Add vegetables.
Bring to a full boil, cover, then simmer 1 hour longer.
Serve in large soup bowls topped with sour cream.

title: rose's chicken
directions: Dip breasts in crumbs.
Brown chicken in garlic butter in large frypan.
Arrange in large casserole, one layer.
In same pan (do not wash), brown mushrooms; add white wine and simmer 3 to 5 minutes to get all juices from pan bottom.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Add enough wine to 1/2 cover.
Dot with small chunks of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Cover if dish appears to be drying out.
Can be made ahead except for baking.

title: pan buckeyes
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together in a microwave; pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt milk chocolate and remaining 1/2 cup peanut butter together and pour over bottom layer.
Refrigerate, then cut into small squares to serve.
Great for a touch of something sweet and chocolate and soooo much easier than Buckeyes!

title: sliced beef barbecue
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Add remaining ingredients, except beef; simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add cooked, thinly sliced beef and serve.

title: zesty caribbean chicken
directions: Combine Crisco, lemon peel, lemon juice, paprika, honey, garlic salt, ginger, oregano and hot pepper sauce in shallow baking dish.
Stir well.
Add chicken.
Coat well.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or up to 4 hours.
(The longer the chicken marinates, the better the chicken will taste.) Turn chicken occasionally.
Broil or grill 3 to 5 minutes per side or until the center is no longer pink.

title: beef casserole
directions: Boil noodles.
Drain and add cream cheese, sour cream, onions and peppers.
Set aside.
Brown chuck, season with seasoned salt and teriyaki sauce.
Add stewed tomatoes and simmer for approximately 10 minutes.

title: healthy slaw(low-fat)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Add to cabbage mixture, tossing well.
Cover and chill.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Better if served after being refrigerated overnight.

title: green bean and mozzarella salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kahlua tiramisu for two
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Arrange ladyfingers in single layer on baking sheet.
Toast in oven for 10 minutes and set aside.
Whisk egg yolks with sugar until smooth and thick in medium bowl.
Whisk in cream cheese.
Fold in whipped cream.
Stir Kahlua into Espresso mixture.
Combine chopped chocolate and cocoa in cup.
Place 2 tablespoons of cream cheese mixture in bottom of two (12 oz.) wine goblets or dessert dishes.
Top each with 3 ladyfingers, 3 to 4 teaspoons of Kahlua mixture and 1/3 cup of cream cheese mixture.
Cover each with 1/4 of chocolate mixture, 3 ladyfingers and 3 to 4 teaspoons of Kahlua mixture.
Top each dessert with 1/2 of remaining cream cheese mixture; smooth top. Sprinkle with remaining chocolate mixture.
Cover and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: club cracker snack
directions: Place crackers in single layer in foil lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. In saucepan, melt butter; add sugar and bring to boil, stirring constantly. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Pour evenly over crackers. Sprinkle with nuts or coconut. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned. Immediately remove from pan, cutting between crackers. Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: bread
directions: Have potato water lukewarm.
Add rest of ingredients and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead until firm.
Let rise until double.
Work down.
Let rise again.
Work into loaves. Bake at 350° until done.

title: honey short bread
directions: With mixer beat butter, honey and vanilla till light and fluffy.
Add flour a cup at a time, beat well after each.
If dough becomes too stiff to stir, knead remaining flour by hand; work in nuts.
Pat dough into shortbread mold on ungreased 9 inch cast iron skillet.
Score the surface with a knife making 24 wedges; with a fork prick deeply into knife score.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes, cool 10 minutes.

title: whiskey killer applesauce(children will love this salad; don't be fooled by the name!)
directions: In a medium sized bowl, dissolve jello, using 2 cups boiling water, then stir in cold water.
In 1/2 cup boiling water, dissolve red hots, then add to jello.
Stir in applesauce. Refrigerate until mixture gels.
Serves 10.

title: fish chowder
directions: Melt butter; add onion, potato, carrot, water, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until carrot is almost tender, about 15 minutes.
Add fish, milk, herbs and remaining 1 teaspoon salt. Heat to simmering.
Cook until fish flakes easily.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Whip cream and then add pudding. Mix well.
Add first ingredients to whipped cream.
Mix well.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts with celery; cool, bone and cut in small pieces.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Mix the two soups, onion, green pepper, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chili powder and garlic salt in a mixing bowl.

title: morocco chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil 4 pieces at a time.
Pour off fat and add onions, stirring frequently.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in paprika, ginger, turmeric, salt and pepper.
Add fresh lemons, chicken, accumulated liquid and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 30 minutes until chicken is tender.
Add olives and salted lemons.
Cover and simmer 4 to 5 minutes.
To serve, arrange chicken on deep platter.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve with rice.

title: microwave sweet and sour franks
directions: Microwave jelly in a serving container until melted, about 30 seconds.
Stir in mustard.
Slice franks into bite-size pieces, then add to jelly mixture.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes until heated through.
Serve warm with toothpicks.

title: dong dingers
directions: Prepare cupcakes; let cool.
Prepare Filling; using super shooter or decorating bag, fill centers of cupcakes with Filling. Dip sparingly into chocolate coating.
Place on waxed paper to cool, allowing coating to harden.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Add enough water to apricot liquid to make 1 cup.
Add to Jell-O mixture; mix well.
Put in refrigerator until it's a soft set.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together; mix well in blender. Add apricots and blend well.
Add Jell-O mixture; mix well.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Refrigerate until well set.
You can use peaches instead of apricots if you want.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes. Put into baking dish that has been buttered on sides and bottom.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, onion salt, salt and pepper and dot the top of potatoes with remainder of butter.
Cover with foil, if using conventional oven, and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles.
Prepare sauce on stove top; cook ground beef until done and add sauce.

When sauce is done, butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and put noodles first, then pour sauce on top and spread all over, then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese evenly on top and place in preheated oven at 350°.
Bake until cheese has been melted on top.

title: edna's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour, soda and cinnamon all mixed together.
Last, add raisins and nuts.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Add soda to hot applesauce. Mix in melted butter. Mix in dry ingredients and add to applesauce mixture.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in 1 stick oleo.
Place in casserole dish and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: graham cracker praline
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Lay graham crackers on sheet. Melt butter and sugar.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add pecans.
Mix well and pour over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° or until mixture bubbles.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Cook pineapple cake.
Then punch holes in layers and pour juice from pineapple over the layers.
Mix ingredients and frost cake.

title: pork chops with mushroom sauce
directions: Broil pork chops for 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Salt and pepper the pork chops and layer the chops and the soup in a casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy fried chicken
directions: Put chicken in a large Ziploc bag or bowl.
Pour in enough marinade to coat chicken. Pour in flour.
Seal bag and mix until chicken is well coated or mix in bowl. Coating will be gummy. Chill to set coating. Spray skillet with Pam.
Add 3 tablespoons oil and heat.
Fry chicken pieces until golden brown on both sides. Add 2 tablespoons water and cook, covered.
If too much chicken to fit in the pan at one time, brown, then put in a baking pan and finish cooking in the oven at 350° for about 20 minutes. Use drippings from pan to make gravy.

title: cookie's six week breakfast muffins
directions: Mix raisin bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in large mixing bowl. Add beaten eggs, shortening and buttermilk.
Mix well. Store in covered container and use as desired.
For Muffins:
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full and bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter will keep for 6 weeks.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat; add spices and onions and cook until onions are soft.
Add olives, corn and 1 can tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add chips and mix, then put into large casserole dish. Pour remaining can of tomato sauce over the top and then the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate custard cake(the birthday cake that gets requested year after year!)
directions: Beat 1 egg and combine with 1/2 cup milk and 2/3 cup sugar. Cook and stir over medium heat about 2 minutes.
Add chocolate bar, broken in pieces.
Reduce heat and cook until chocolate is melted and mixture thickens.
Cool to room temperature.

title: plum strawberry bread
directions: Combine raisins, brandy or grape juice and enough water to cover raisins in a saucepan.
Bring back to a simmer, cool and drain.
Grease and flour three 5 x 9-inch loaf pans or muffins. Mash or chop strawberries.
Combine with remaining wet ingredients and stir.
Combine with dry ingredients and mix well.
Divide evenly among pans and bake for about 1 hour.

title: pink salad
directions: Pour dry Jell-O mix in bowl and stir in drained pineapple. Add cottage cheese and stir well.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well. Chill and serve.

title: no-salt herb blend
directions: Mix and store in tightly covered jar.
Use on tomatoes, cold, raw or cooked vegetables or anything that needs a little extra flavor.

title: healthy cookies
directions: Smash bananas; mix all ingredients together.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.
Put rack up 2nd from the top.
Cookies can easily get overcooked.

title: bread for all seasons(like a cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flours, sugars, cinnamon, soda and salt in large bowl.
Beat eggs, oil and vanilla in small bowl; add to dry ingredients and blend.
Stir in carrots, apple or zucchini, chips and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 6-cup or 8-cup bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes; remove from pan.
If desired, spread with Cream Cheese Glaze.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Melt butter; spoon in egg, cake mix and nuts.
This will form a thick pastry.
Press in greased cake pan.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in bottom of pan.
Pour dry cake mix over this.
Spread nuts on top of this.
Melt butter; pour over top.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into uncooked pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
This makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Roll into balls.
Melt wax and chocolate until bubbly.
Dip each ball into chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat cast-iron skillet and sprinkle with about one teaspoon corn meal.
Mix together the corn meal, egg, milk and oil.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into skillet and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chips and cheese.
Put in an ungreased casserole dish.
Put cheese on top and cover with crushed chips.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: mesclun salad
directions: Carefully rinse and pat dry the baby greens.
Place in a large salad bowl.
Pour the 1/4 cup vinegar into a small mixing bowl.
Pour the olive oil into the vinegar in a thin, steady steam, whisking continually until the olive oil has been incorporated into the vinegar.
Whisk in the sugar and minced garlic.
Toss gently into the greens.
Serve the pine nuts in a small bowl on the side of the salad.

title: green been and corn casserole
directions: Mix corn and green beans in greased dish.
Combine soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, onions and salt and pour over corn and beans.
Spread crackers, almonds and margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: In medium glass bowl, blend sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 or 3 minutes or until to a full boil.
Stir in cereal and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper or shape into balls.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: fast chili
directions: Brown ground beef, celery and onion.
Add tomato soup and beans.
Mix well.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder to taste. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, vanilla and egg until light and fluffy.
Mix flour with soda and salt.
Blend into shortening mixture.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop 2 inches apart from teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 50.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Mix first
7 ingredients in saucepan. Bring to boil and simmer for
minute.
Pour
hot mixture over tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Cover
and place in refrigerator to chill. Before serving,
add
cucumber.
Serve
very cold on lettuce. Serves 8 to 10.

title: 30-day coleslaw
directions: Boil ingredients.
Add to 1/2 head green and red cabbage, sliced.
Pour hot over mixture and do not stir for 2 hours.
Best 2nd day.
Can be refrigerated 30 days.

title: shish kabob
directions: Cut the meat in cubes and cut the onion in cubes, then cut the green pepper and cut the tomato in cubes and put the salt and pepper on the meat before cooking.
Then get the barbecue sticks and put one cube of meat and one cube of onion and one cube of green pepper and one cube of tomato and repeat that until you finish all and then put them on the barbecue.
Enjoy.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until soft; debone and cut into quarters.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put everything together in a pot.

title: chocolate-cherry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Stir cake mix and evaporated milk in a bowl just until mix is moistened.
Spread in prepared pan.
Pour pie filling evenly over top (most fruit will sink).
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with walnuts and bake 20 minutes longer until nuts are toasted.

title: christina's no bake cookies
directions: In a 6-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes, then add 1 1/2 cups peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Drop on wax paper; set until firm.

title: orange jello
directions: Use only half the amount of water called for on the jello box. Pour into mold and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups of chicken stock, following directions on package.
Mix all ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Tear 1/2 of cake into small pieces and layer bowl.
Put 1/2 of prepared pudding mix over cake.
Put 1 can of pie filling over pudding.
Put 1/2 of drained pineapple over pudding.
Repeat all 4 layers as above.
Refrigerate over night and top with Cool Whip just before serving.
If you want to make a smaller cake use, 1 large box pudding, 1 can pie filling and 1 large can crushed pineapple, drained.

title: frito salad
directions: Toss all ingredients except salad dressing and Fritos.
Add dressing and Fritos when ready to serve.

title: cherokee casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Drain.
Add onion and cook until tender. Add tomatoes, soup, rice and seasonings.
Let simmer about 5 minutes or longer if it seems too juicy.
Remove bay leaf and pour into casserole dish.
Top with sliced Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° until the cheese is browned.
Freezes well.

title: almond skillet coffee cake
directions: Melt butter and add to sugar in mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and flavoring and mix well.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie crusts as directed on package.

title: chicken fajitas casserole
directions: Saute pepper, onion and chicken until almost done.
Put all in bottom of casserole.
Add layer of picante.
Top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, tortilla chips or rice.
Serves 4.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix on medium-high speed until smooth and creamy. Use as a sour cream substitute.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt margarine in pan.
Sprinkle crumbs, coconut and chips.
Pour milk over all and sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in refrigerator before cutting.

title: banana oatmeal muffins(lo-cal)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a large mixing bowl, stir together oats and milk, then let stand 15 minutes.

title: citrus seafood salad
directions: Brush 1 tablespoon of oil on cod. Bake on greased baking sheet in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until fish flakes. Mix all ingredients together except red onions. Mix cod and juice mixture well, then spoon into individual servings and garnish with red onion rings.

title: microwave hamburger stroganoff
directions: In microwave on High, brown ground chuck and onion (covered); drain grease.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream and milk.
Mix well.

title: oriental chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or large, heavy skillet.
Stir-fry chicken over moderate heat for 5 minutes, until opaque.
Skim chicken from pan.
Set aside.
Stir-fry broccoli, red bell pepper, mushrooms and scallions for 3 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: In large heavy boiler combine flour, sugar, pineapple, and whipping cream. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat, add margarine, stir until melted. Refrigerate until cool. Fold apples, raisins, and nuts into flour-pineapple mixture. Chill 3 hours.

title: red chili powder
directions: You will need a blender.

title: grandma annie kimmel's yellow cake
directions: Sift flour and measure; sift again with baking powder and salt.
Cream butter, sugar and extract until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in well-greased tube pan for 1 hour or until pick comes clean in 350° oven.
Keeps very well and is super with fruit, ice cream or as a base for trifle.
(From Connecticut.)

title: ingrid's stuffed steaks
directions: Wash steaks in cold water and dry good with paper towels.
Salt and pepper (season well).
Spread mustard on one side.
Slice onions in rings and cover steaks.
Cut up small dill pickles and put on steaks.
Wrap 1 wide or 2 narrow strips of bacon on steaks. Roll them (use toothpicks or thread).
Fry in 4-quart kettle with margarine (over 1/2 stick margarine for 2 steaks).
Let margarine get good and hot, and put steaks in to fry so they are golden brown on both sides.
When done, put a little hot water in so the brown grease loosens from kettle, then add a little water as it cooks.

title: bacon and tomato spread
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms; cut off stems, leaving 1/4-inch. Heat water to boiling.
Add mushrooms.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and cool mushrooms.
Place in bowl.
Pour marinade over mushrooms.
Toss until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate up to 1 week, stirring occasionally.
To serve, drain mushrooms well, 7 calories per mushroom.

title: squash casserole(this was my granny green's recipe.)
directions: Beat eggs well and add to squash.
Add 1/2 cup of Miracle Whip. Saute onion and peppers in a small skillet with butter.
Pour peppers, onions and remaining butter into squash.
Stir in grated cheese and salt and pepper to taste.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour and baking powder.
Heat oven to 500°.
Mix in buttermilk.
Put 2 tablespoons butter into 1/4 cup measure and fill with shortening.
Melt butter/margarine mixture in oven in iron skillet.
Shape dough into biscuits with hands; add more flour if dough is sticky.
Place biscuits into skillet and turn to coat.
Bake 10 minutes at 500°.

title: caponata
directions: Cut eggplant quarters into 1/2-inch slices.
In colander, sprinkle with salt and drain one hour.
In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stir vinegar and sugar until dissolved.
Stir in tomato paste, basil, olives and capers.
Continue heating, stirring occasionally until thickened (about 20 minutes).
In large skillet, heat 1/3 cup oil and fry single layers of eggplant (both sides) until brown, adding more oil as needed until all is cooked.
In same pan, add 2 tablespoons oil.
Over low heat, cook vegetables until tender.
Add tomato mixture and eggplant.
Toss gently. Chill.
Serve with rye bread or pumpernickel.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix in remaining ingredients, topping with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: emergency cake topping for yellow cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and canned milk; heat on stove.
Add coconut.
Spread on cake and put under broiler in oven for 3 minutes.
(Double ingredients for sheet cake.)

title: onion dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine soup and sour cream. Cover. Refrigerate until serving time, at least 2 hours. Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly with your hands.
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet until done.
Drain well.
Add brown sugar, mustard, ketchup and relish.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add cheese, cover and let stand for 5 minutes, then serve.

title: beef stew
directions: Chop vegetables into chunks.
Mix everything together.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 4 hours.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add lentils.
Cook a little longer. While beans are cooking, dice and saute onions.
Add tomatoes and salsa.
Add sauce mixture to beans.
Simmer over low heat until the cornbread is ready.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk until smooth. Gently stir in 2 cups Cool Whip and candy bar. Set aside. Pour 1 3/4 cups milk into a bowl. Add pudding mixes and beat. Stir in 1/2 cup Cool Whip. Spread 1/2 the pudding mixture on bottom crust. Spread cream cheese mix over pudding. Top with remaining pudding mixture. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove chicken, cool and bone.
Add celery, carrots, onion and limas to broth and cook until just fork-tender.

title: sausage casserole for 6
directions: Crumble sausage and cook slowly until brown.
Remove from pan and drain.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in salted water until done.
Add butter, cheese, slightly beaten egg yolks and milk.
Stir until melted and smooth. Beat egg whites until stiff; add grits mixture to egg whites. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake for 1 hour at 325°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley. Dip chicken breast or chicken strips in milk and breadcrumb mixture. Put in baking dish. Combine butter, garlic and lemon juice and drizzle over chicken. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine and stir to mix all ingredients and put in pie crust. Bake at 475°
for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake another 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: caramel apples
directions: You will need 6 wooden popsicle sticks.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine in a bowl 1/2 cup milk, egg and margarine.
Add grated rind and juice of 1/2 orange, chopped apples and vanilla.
Sift together cake flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in milk mixture with a spoon until blended.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into 1/2 inch hot oil.
Fry to a golden brown.
Drain.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar thoroughly. Gradually add granulated sugar; continue creaming.	Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.	Sift baking powder and salt with flour; add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla, then nuts, and blend well. Turn batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 90 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with spoon.
Add sugar and beat with spoon.
Add flour and mix.
Add Karo syrup and melted butter and cool.
Add vanilla, salt and cream.
Mix with spoon good.
Put in pie shell and bake @ 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls (golobki)
directions: Using large pot, cook the cabbage until you can remove the outer leaves without breaking them.

(You may remove the thick stem in the center of each leaf to make for ease in rolling.) Keep steaming your cabbage until you can no longer use the smaller inner leaves, saving them for creamed cabbage.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all together and chill.

title: potato chowder
directions: In large kettle, combine potatoes, carrots, onion, pepper, parsley and bouillon cubes.
Just cover vegetables with water and cook until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not drain.

title: poppy seed carrot soup
directions: Melt the margarine in a large, heavy saucepan.
Add the onion; saute until the onion is translucent.

Add the chicken broth, water, carrots, rice, thyme, pepper and salt; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until the mixture comes to a boil. Reduce the heat to low; cover the pan and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat; let cool for 15 minutes.
Place half of the mixture in a blender; puree until smooth.
Transfer to a clean saucepan.
Repeat the process with the other half.

title: no bake cake
directions: Crumble cake and spread evenly in bottom of a large oblong pan.
Pour pineapple evenly over cake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion, salt and pepper and broccoli. Pour into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top. Melt 3/4 stick of butter, mix well with stuffing mix and sprinkle on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach rockefeller
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well except tomatoes.
Cut thick slices of tomatoes and layer them on the bottom of baking dish (13 x 9-inch dish).
Sprinkle tomatoes with garlic powder.
Top tomatoes with spinach mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: homemade eagle brand milk
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
This is equal to 1 can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pat 1 cup crushed potato chips on top. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: microwave twice baked potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in microsafe dish, then poke them with a fork a few times.
Microwave, uncovered, for 10 minutes on High, then arrange the potatoes upside-down (after 5 minutes).
After cooked for 10 minutes, take out and cover on counter to continue cooking. Mix butter and green onion in microwave until tender.
Cook bacon in microwave until crisp for 4 to 5 minutes.
Then crumble.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out pulp.
Mash potatoes with butter and green onion mixture, milk and seasonings until light fluffy. Add bacon; spoon potato mixture into shells.
Arrange on dish and sprinkle with cheeses.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 5 minutes or until cheeses are melted.
Rotate dish after half the cooking time.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly and gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt, and fold into the first mixture. Add apples and nut meats, cut fine. If desired a dash of cinnamon may be added here. Place mixture in a well greased pie pan and bake
350° for about 40 minutes. Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: low carb meat loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Combine tomato paste, water, garlic, basil, oregano and salt in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low. Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine turkey, oatmeal, egg substitute, zucchini and 1/2 c. of the tomato mixture. Mix well. Shape into a loaf and place into an ungreased loaf pan. Bake for 45 minutes. Discard any drippings. Pour 1/2 c. of the remaining tomato mixture over the top of the loaf. Bake for an additional 15 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before slicing. Serve remaining tomato sauce on the side. This has 12 grams carbohydrate.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve over ice.

title: microwave zucchini nut bread
directions: Grease 6-cup microproof ring mold.
Sprinkle mixture of 2 teaspoons of sugar and cinnamon over greased surface, shake to spread evenly, discarding excess.
Beat together eggs, remaining sugar, oil, yogurt, vanilla and zucchini.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into prepared mold.
Cook on 70 (Roast) 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Rotate dish if bread appears to be rising unevenly. Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.
Serves 12 to 18.
Total cooking time:
15 minutes.

title: hot lemonade spritzer
directions: Heat water to boiling; add lemonade and cinnamon disks. Refreshing taste.

title: wet bottom shoo-fly pie
directions: Crumb together flour, shortening and brown sugar.
Set aside 3/4 cup crumbs.
Add syrups, egg, water and soda to remaining crumbs.
Pour into 10-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with crumbs over mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put in bottom of buttered 10 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer both cans of soup next.
Then put a layer of squash.
Top with crushed cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
The cheese can go on the last 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into greased pan.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend well.
It is ready to serve.
This will keep in the refrigerator for several days.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Beat cream cheese on medium speed until creamy.
Slowly add milk and pudding.
Beat until smooth.
Add all but 9 cookies. (These are for decoration.)
Beat until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and beat until well blended in.
Pour the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use remaining cookies on top.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: pork hash
directions: Add all ingredients together except the wrappers.
Do not mix too long, just enough to combine the ingredients.
Add one tablespoon of filling to the center of each wrapper and bring edges up, forming a cup.
Coat bottom and sides with a little vegetable oil so they don't stick to the steaming pan.
Place in pan and steam for about 30-45 minutes.
I use my rice cooker to steam the pork hash!

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice and cook fresh carrots.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and pour over carrots.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: almond asparagus
directions: Wash asparagus; cut into 1-inch diagonal slices.
Heat butter in skillet; add asparagus and saute 3-4 minutes.
Cover skillet and steam about 2 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Toss asparagus with lemon juice and almonds; salt & pepper to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: In container of blender combine chocolate bits, eggs, coffee, rum or orange flavored
liqueur, and milk.
Blend mixture at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour mousse into 4 dessert cups and chill.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Blend flavors well if made ahead of serving time.

title: four pepper salsa with chips
directions: Combine first 13 ingredients in processor. Finely chop using on/off turns. Transfer to bowl. Cover and chill at least 4 hours. (Can be made 2 days ahead.)
Mix cilantro into salsa. Serve with chips.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight; drain.
Add fresh water.
Cook slowly with ham bone for 2 hours.
Add onions, celery salt, seasoned salt, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Remove ham bone; trim off any meat and return to pot.
Add ham bits and simmer for 1 hour.
This is the bean soup they serve at Amish Acres.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat Eagle Brand, lemon juice and egg yolks well.
Pour into crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar and beat until stiff again.
Pile onto pie. Bake at 325° until meringue is browned.
Pie must be kept refrigerated.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Roll out on a floured board. Cut out.
Bake in a 400°
oven until brown.

title: fiesta spread
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, green pepper and garlic. Drain. Add next four ingredients. Mash in beans. Heat, stirring frequently. Add Tabasco to taste. Garnish with cheese and if desired, olives. Serve warm with Ritz crackers.

title: hopping john
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain grease and set beef aside.
Fry the bacon; set aside.
Pour bacon grease into ground beef.
Cook rice.
Mix cooked rice and ground beef together.
Cut up bacon; add it to mixture.
Add a little green chilies, along with its juice, to desired hotness.
Add the black-eyed peas.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tori tori(chicken)
directions: Cut up a whole chicken or use chicken parts.
Clean thoroughly.
Season chicken to taste with the seasoning blend, then arrange in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Trim excess fat from the oxtails (unless you love fat!) and place in a large pot.
Fill with water to cover the oxtails and more. Add everything but the potatoes, carrots and whiskey to the pot.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 1/2 hours or more, until peanuts are tender the meat almost but not quite falls off the bone.
If you can wait, cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffing for celery
directions: Mix together and stuff celery pieces.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients, except oats, flour and raisins.
Stir in oats, flour and raisins.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, about 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: *blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Blue cheese; blend well. Gently stir in Blue cheese.
Refrigerate until needed.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar until well mixed.
Add flour, cinnamon and diced apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, flour, salt and vanilla. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover pastry edges with foil to keep from burning.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover bottom of cookie sheet with crescents.
Press together separations.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.
Mix yogurt, cream cheese and dressing until smooth and spread over crust.
Cover with vegetables and cheese.
Bake to melt cheese.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Store in container with tight lid.
Use 1/4 cup of mixture in cup of hot water.

title: chili-chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with chips; set aside.
In large skillet over medium heat, saute chicken, onion and garlic in oil until chicken is opaque.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheeses, until blended.
Pour over chips; top with cheeses.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through and cheeses melt.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil in a small bowl.
Stir flour, sugar, apples, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Combine egg mixture to flour mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: This salad should
be
made
to 48 hours before you plan to serve it.
(I like to use the sweet/sour kraut.)

title: colorado crepes
directions: Mix ingredients quickly; don't overbeat.
Blend eggs, salt, sugar and milk in blender.
Gradually add flour, blending after each addition.
Add and blend melted margarine.
Heat a nonstick lightly greased 10-inch skillet.
Add a small quantity of batter. Tip the skillet and let the batter spread to cover entire pan. Cook over moderate heat.
When edges dry and underneath is lightly brown, reverse it and brown other side. Roll pancake up.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: freezer waffles
directions: Combine egg yolks, milk and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients. Fold in stiff egg whites.
Cook in waffle iron.
Cool.
Place wax paper between.
Store in heavy foil.
Reheat at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken lynn
directions: Boil chicken until tender and cut in bite size pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Mix with chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers, sprinkle over top.
Dribble margarine over cracker topping and sprinkle with seed.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
If in refrigerator it will take longer to get bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add rice.
Cook broccoli and chop.
Mix the soups, broccoli and rice.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy, then beat in the eggs.
In a small bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and pudding mix.
Gradually add this to the first combination.
Stir in the chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
May use butterscotch mix and chips.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
In a sauce pan heat sugar in water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until fine and crumbly.
Add milk and stir with fork only until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface, knead just until smooth.
Roll out into a large rectangle about 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples and apples over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Dampen the edge of the dough with a little water and seal.
Slice into about 16 slices 1/2 inch thick.
Place in pan, pour sugar syrup around rolls.
Bake for 55 -60 min.
Great with ice cream.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Chill, covered, before serving.

title: grandma's hungarian liver stuffing
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix with all other ingredients. Stuff into turkey.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine ground chuck, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce; mix well and pack into a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup tomato sauce with remaining ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
While baking, spoon sauce over meat loaf several times.

title: lunch box pies
directions: Using a favorite pie crust recipe, cut rolled pie crust into large circles with a large cookie cutter or rim of a coffee can. Place 1/4 cup of any canned fruit pie filling in center of each circle.

Moisten edges of the dough with water and fold dough over to make a semi-circle, pressing edges together with fork tines. Bake in hot oven for about 30 minutes at 350°, until golden. Sprinkle with 10x sugar, if desired.
Makes 8 pies.

title: peanut butter snack
directions: In medium size bowl, put peanut butter, powdered sugar and corn syrup.
Mix well and eat with fork or spoon.

title: creamy ginger dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 1 cup.

title: easy muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into 12-greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: In a bowl beat margarine with an electric mixer until softened.
Add about 1/2 of the flour, sugar, egg, vanilla, baking soda and cream of tartar to margarine.
Beat until combined.
Stir in remaining flour.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: three vegetable salad
directions: Break or cut.
Put in bowl.
Salt to taste.
Add mayonnaise to taste (as desired).
Mix all of this together and ready to eat.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut up head of cabbage and add to hot bacon drippings.
Cook over medium heat, covered, until tender.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Makes an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: breakfast pudding (eich milch)
directions: Warm 2 cups milk in a heavy pan or skillet.
Meanwhile, mix 1 cup milk with the other ingredients and add to the warm milk. Cook, stirring often until mixture is slightly thickened and serve with toast.

title: berries on the square
directions: Arrange 9 of the crackers in bottom of a 9-inch square pan. Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package for pudding. Fold in whipped topping.
Pour half the pudding mixture over crackers in pan and top with strawberries.
Arrange remaining crackers on the berries and add remaining pudding mixture.
Spread remaining whipped topping over the top and garnish with additional strawberries, if desired.
Chill.
Yields 9 servings.

title: sweet potato nut balls
directions: Combine potatoes, orange juice and sugar. Blend well. Shape into 12 balls, using about 2 tablespoons for each ball. Roll balls in pecans. Place on cookie sheet and heat in 350° oven 15 or 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add cake mix (dry mix), 1/3 at a time; mix well.
If mixer is used, add last part of cake mix by hand.
Chill dough for 30 minutes. Heat oven to 375°.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add peanut butter and cream until smooth.
Add sugar and cream until mixture is light and fluffy. Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix the ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Make balls the size of walnuts and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: yummy balls
directions: Combine meat, onion, rice cracker crumbs, egg, salt and pepper to taste, cayenne pepper and chili powder and Italian seasoning.
Shape into golf ball size balls.
Place in a lightly greased casserole or pan, in one layer.
Mix the soup and the water and pour over the Yummy Balls.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn. Mix together and put in a greased casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese, onion and salt.
Spread over beans and corn. Mix 1 roll of Ritz crackers (crushed) with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spread on top of the casserole.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: franks and noodle casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion and seasoning in butter.
Stir in soup, milk and tomatoes; add noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes and serve.

title: cherry pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Mix with cherries. Turn into pie pan. Dot with butter and sprinkle extract on top.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slits in crust. Sprinkle with sugar. Cover edges of crust with aluminum foil. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes. Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: sausage apple bake
directions: Cut sausage at 1 1/2-inch intervals, but do not cut all the way through.
Set aside.

title: yankee donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour; beat well.
Add enough flour (all-purpose) to make soft dough.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick; cut out and fry in hot grease.

title: greenbrier salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in boiling water. Cool. Add crushed pineapple and cottage cheese. Place in bowl and chill overnight.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Drain salmon; reserve liquid.
Flake salmon and set aside. In a pot, cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Blend in flour; add milk and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
In another pot, combine tomato juice and salt.
Cook until heated; add to milk mixture.
Blend in salmon and liquid.
Heat and serve.

title: berry mallow yam bake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, oats and cinnamon; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Lightly toss 1 cup crumb mixture with yams and cranberries; arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Chill well before serving. Serves 8.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Blend in large bowl the cheese, soup and milk. Cook onion in butter until tender.
Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Add onion, broccoli, ham, rice and Worcestershire to soup mix.
Makes 2 (1 1/2-quart) casseroles.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese souffle
directions: This is a good vehicle to which a few vegetables or ham can be added.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak for 10 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add next 2 ingredients. Push meat aside and add onion, green peppers and mushrooms.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add water with cornstarch to sauce.
Serve on hot rice or noodles.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian christmas bread
directions: In bowl of electric mixer dissolve yeast in water.
Add honey, sweetener, salt, butter and half the flour.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed on mixer or 300 strokes by hand.
Add remaining flour to fruit and nuts and add to yeast mixture along with the anise and vanilla.
Blend well.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Stir down batter.
Spread in 2 well buttered 1 pound coffee cans.
Let rise until batter reaches 3/4 inch from top.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Yields 12 slices per loaf, 80 calories per slice using sweetener (82 calories using sugar).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and boil in seasoned water until tender.
Melt oleo in pan and coat croutons.
Put 1/2 of croutons in baking dish. Mix all other ingredients and put over croutons.
Sprinkle other croutons on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pearline's baked tomatoes
directions: Pour juice off tomatoes. Mix together tomatoes, bread crumbs, chopped onion, sugar, red pepper, salt, garlic and 1/2 stick of butter. Pour into greased casserole. Dot rest of butter on top; add cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes or until set. Serves 4.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Chop dried beef into small pieces. Combine with softened cream cheese, milk, onions, dill weed and salt, mixing until smooth. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: favorite chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Add chopped vegetables with the seasoning packet.
Combine soup, milk and parsley and set aside in 2 to 3-quart baking dish, arrange stuffing across center of dish. Spoon thin layer of soup mixture in casserole on each side of stuffing.
Arrange chicken over soup mixture and overlap as needed.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Uncover, bake 10 minutes more.
Stir sauce and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Heat peanut oil in a wok and saute shrimp until pink. Add broccoli, sugar, ginger, sherry, sesame oil, salt and pepper. Saute for several minutes. Combine water and cornstarch and add to mixture; cook until thickens. Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: cream puffssocorro, new mexico
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil; stir in flour, all at once.
Beat in eggs, all at one time, until smooth.
Drop dough by tsp. onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Keep 3 inches apart.
Cut in half and fill with cream.

title: working woman's stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onions.
Add soup, sour cream and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.
Goes well with French bread and a tossed salad.

title: peas and rice
directions: Cook rice and bacon; set aside.
In skillet, add butter, garlic and onion.
Cut bacon into small pieces; add to skillet.
Saute until onion is done.
Add rice and peas.
Mix until coated.
Salt and pepper to taste.
"Enjoy."

title: potato soup
directions: Cook onion, potatoes and butter in water to cover, until tender.
Blend flour with milk until smooth.
Add to potato mixture.
Cook until boiling, about 1 minute.
