Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine butter and marshmallows in heavy 2 or 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows melt.
Add to popcorn, candy and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Press mixture into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Chill until firm.
Invert cake onto serving plate and garnish with gumdrop flowers, if desired.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
While still hot, add 1 tsp. vanilla, 1/2 cup peanut butter and 3 cups quick oats.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let set until hard.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients and serve cold.

title: breaded veal slices
directions: After fish have been cleaned, remove skins.
Soak the fish in a solution of beaten egg and milk, then flour, cracker crumbs or cornmeal may be used to coat the fish.
Salt and pepper to taste and fry in a skillet or deep fryer for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with tartar sauce or ketchup.

title: yankee quahog chowder
directions: In a frying pan render sliced salt pork.
When fat is rendered, add onions and saute until golden brown on edges. Strain quahogs and reserve juice.
Measure juice and add water to double the amount.
Put liquid in large saucepan.
Add onions, fat and cracklings.
Bring to simmer and add potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are nearly tender.
In food processor, pulse quahogs until chopped (not too fine).
Add to saucepan; rinse processor bowl with a little water and add (good Yankees don't waste a drop!).
Simmer chowder a few minutes until clams are cooked.
Let diners add butter and warm milk to taste at the table.

title: apple crunch
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in well-greased pan.
Combine brown sugar, flour, margarine and quick cooking oats.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: smoked salmon and brie pizza
directions: Place pizza shell on a baking sheet.
With a sharp knife, cut rind from cheese, wetting knife often to prevent sticking.
Cut cheese in small hunks and arrange over pizza shell.
Bake at 450° for five minutes or until cheese is about half melted.
Arrange smoked salmon over cheese.
Sprinkle with dill.
Return to oven and bake three to four minutes longer.
Let stand at room temperature for five minutes before cutting.

title: christmas creme de cacao balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine crushed cookies, nuts and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Add creme de cacao and corn syrup and mix thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and roll each in powdered sugar.
Place in airtight container and chill overnight. Makes 3 dozen balls.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Make a white sauce out of the butter, flour, salt, pepper, soup or ham base and milk. Cook until thick.
Layer potatoes, onions and sauce in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on Medium-high 17 to 19 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pink dessert
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Fold in the Cool Whip and nuts and/or coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, except the ketchup and bacon.
Mix thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan; cover with 3 strips of bacon.
Pour over all one (8 ounce) can tomato sauce. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves approximately 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Rinse chicken under cool water.
Place in large pot and fill with water about 1 inch over top of chicken.
Add 1/2 stick of butter and cook for about 1 hour.
(Test:
Chicken should fall easily off bone.)
Chop or shred chicken.
Save 2 cups of the chicken broth.
Boil eggs for 10 minutes.
Remove shells.
Chop into fine pieces.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop, prepare and measure remaining ingredients.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon.
Pour into a casserole dish and apply 4 slices uncooked bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: party punch
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water; add juices and cold water. Stir in the ice just until melted. Spoon in the sherbet.

title: french fried onions
directions: Slice onions thin. Soak in cold water. Drain and soak in milk. Add to batter of remaining ingredients. Drop in deep fat and fry. Drain on paper towel. Serve.

title: cookie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat flour, butter, sugar and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press firmly into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with filling; finish baking as directed.

title: reese's peanut butter cup
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips with 1 tablespoon butter.
Spread over cooled mixture.

title: berlena's old-fashioned fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add margarine.
Add raisins; mix well. Add all chopped fruits gradually.
Add pecans and flavorings; mix well.
Add rest of fruits.
Add flour and work in well with hands. Must be mixed well.
If too dry, add some sweet milk.
Should not be able to pour it in pan.
Use hands to put it in pan.
Bundt cake pan can be used, lined with wax paper (on bottom and sides). Do not grease paper or pan.
Put mix in pan (should be about 3/4 full).
Cover top of pan with wax paper.
Tie with string.
Make sure fruit cake mix is completely covered on top and sides with paper so no water can get in.
Put cake on rack in canner; make sure it is level.
Put enough water to cover bottom of pan.
(Add water if necessary.)
Steam 3 hours on medium heat.
Keep top on canner.
Never let water run out.

title: wish-bone salad
directions: In large pan, cook macaroni just until it turns white.
Drain and run under cold water.
Pour salad dressing over macaroni and stir well.
Put into a large bowl (macaroni will swell up as it sits).
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, toss macaroni with remaining ingredients.
Serve cold.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put oatmeal to egg in small bowl.
Put hamburger meat in large mixing bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons A.1.
Mix together, then add the onion and bell pepper; mix together.

title: spinach noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cut deboned chicken into fairly large pieces; save broth.
Cook vegetables in broth; drain and save remaining broth for cooking noodles.
Cook noodles according to package directions; noodles should have absorbed most of the broth.
Add mushrooms with juice, water chestnuts, cheese, vegetables and chicken.
Mix well; add salt and pepper to taste. Place in buttered casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly.
This is better if made a day ahead of serving.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: twins delight
directions: Cut Twins into 2 layers.
Place bottom halves in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with pudding, pineapple and the remaining Twins.
Spread whipped topping on top and refrigerate until serving.

title: texas beans
directions: Cook beef, onion, green pepper and salt in skillet until brown.
Add onion soup, tomatoes, pinto beans and white beans. Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: fried perch or small bass
directions: Dip dry fillets in evaporated milk and sprinkle corn flake crumbs on each side.
Let sit for 10 to 15 minutes to dry.
May be done ahead of time, 1 to 2 hours, and put in refrigerator until ready to cook.
Fry at 380° in electric skillet in about 1 to 2 inches of oil until brown (about 3 to 8 minutes per side).
Drain on paper towel.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Place noodles in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix beef, Ragu sauce, sugar, salt and garlic salt together and pour over noodles.
Add Mozzarella cheese on top of sauce.
Mix cottage cheese and onions. Pour over Mozzarella cheese.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: sour cream custard sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the eggs, milk, sugar and salt. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture coats a metal spoon. Pour custard mixture into a medium bowl; set inside a larger bowl filled with ice.
Stir in the vanilla.
Continue stirring 1 to 2 minutes.
Gradually stir custard into sour cream; cover and chill. Serve over desired fresh fruit.
Makes 3 1/4 cups.

title: date bran muffins
directions: Mix boiling water, soda and margarine; let cool.
Add sugar, eggs and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: One layer of onion, one layer of bacon and one layer of peppers in each piece of meat.
Roll up and tie with thread. Brown on both sides in 2 kettles.
Make four packages of brown gravy and two packages of mushroom gravy.
Add to meat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sirloin steak with peppercorn sauce
directions: Brush medium-sized nonstick skillet with vegetable oil.
Place steak in skillet over medium heat and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until of desired doneness, turning occasionally to brown beef evenly on both sides.
Remove from skillet; keep warm in a 200° oven.

title: float
directions: Cook until thick and add egg whites well beaten.

title: chow mein (hamburger)
directions: Mix and simmer the above ingredients over medium heat.
Pour over hot steamed rice. Top with chow mein noodles.

title: ham bean soup
directions: Rinse beans, then cover with water and add 2 tablespoons salt to taste.
Cover and soak overnight or may bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and soak for 1 hour.
Drain water.
Add to beans 2-quarts water, bay leaves, basil, onion (coarsely chopped) and ham bone.
Boil slowly, covered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add tomatoes, juice and all.
Simmer about 1/2 hour more, covered.
Remove ham bone, putting back into soup any ham still clinging to bone.
Serve hot.

title: sheet cake
directions: Put oleo and water in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Stir well and then add buttermilk, soda, cinnamon, slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 16 x 11-inch or 18 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: baked cubed beef casserole
directions: Brown cubed beef.
Saute onion.
Add to other ingredients. Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Heat sugar, milk and salt.
When bubbles form on edge of pan, cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add chocolate pieces, vanilla and marshmallows.
Add 1 cup nuts if desired.
Pour into pan.
Cool.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, thoroughly.
Mold into steak shapes about 1 1/4-inch thick.
Place in buttered baking dish and brush melted butter on tops.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for about 25 minutes longer.
(At this time, turn the steaks over.)
Brush with more butter once or twice during this baking.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix chopped onion rings and cheese.
Wash chicken.
Dry with toweling.
Dip in garlic butter.
Roll in onion ring mixture. Place in appropriate size baking pan so that the chicken is tightly together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until center of chicken is done.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add juice and bananas which have been mashed thoroughly.
Mix well.
Add soda when ready to serve.
This can be frozen in containers.
Then just add soda after it thaws. Makes about 60 servings.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions; let stand overnight with salt sprinkled on them.
Drain.
Add sugar, water, spice and vinegar. Cook until tender (5 minutes).
Pour hot pickles and juice into hot jars and seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: artichoke spinach cheese casserole
directions: Put artichoke hearts in medium casserole.
Squeeze spinach dry and arrange evenly over artichoke hearts.
Beat cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Spread over spinach; add pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Also freezes well.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Cook onion and celery in little butter until limp.
Mix all but
stuffing.
Put in 2 casseroles.
Top
with
stuffing which has been mixed with 1 stick melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage; reserve.
In 9 x 12-inch pan, place croutons; top with Cheddar cheese.
Layer sausage evenly on top. Blend eggs, onion, peppers, mushrooms and 2 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over sausage and refrigerate overnight.

title: tang pie
directions: Blend Eagle Brand milk, sour cream and Tang together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill. Top with Cool Whip and pecans. Serve.

title: oven dirty rice
directions: Mix well. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chinese style vegetables
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet or wok.
Add broccoli and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes, until vegetables are bright green.
Add broth and soy sauce.
Simmer uncovered about 3 minutes.
Garnish with almonds or seeds.
Great with other fresh vegetables - green beans and celery.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts (set aside).
Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Mix in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes and test.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans. Turn onto rack and cool.

title: peach bake
directions: Mix juice from peaches with cornstarch or flour to thicken. Add cinnamon.
Place peaches in baking dish.
Sprinkle with Molly McButter and top with gingersnaps and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until sugar has melted.

title: hot cider
directions: Combine cider and all of the other ingredients.
Boil 10 minutes in a covered pan.
Strain.
Serve hot.

title: homemade pizza sauce
directions: Saute finely chopped onions and garlic in the olive oil. Add the remaining ingredients and slow cook for approximately 1 hour.

title: quick chili beans
directions: Brown diced onions and garlic in skillet.
Add hamburger and cook until completely browned; drain off excess grease.
Add garlic salt and black pepper to taste.
Wash pinto beans in colander; drain.
In large pot, combine beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Bring to a low boil.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add meat and onion mixture to beans.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes more.
Stir well.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on package; cool. Combine with other ingredients.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel and slice onions thin.
Saute in margarine until transparent.
Add all other ingredients; simmer for 1 to 4 hours. (The longer, the better.)
Serve plain or in onion soup crocks with a slice of French bread.
Sprinkle with a little Parmesan cheese (optional).
Fill crocks with soup; cover with 1 slice of Swiss cheese.
Put in hot oven at 400° until cheese melts and bubbles (only takes a few minutes).
Bon appetit.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove the core from the cabbage by cutting around it with a sharp knife. Cover cabbage with water and boil until leaves fall apart. Take the leaves out of water as they fall apart. Cool. Fry salt pork slowly. After melted, add onion and fry until done. Combine meat, rice, onion mixture, parsley, green pepper and tomato sauce and mix thoroughly. Place a spoonful of filling on each leaf and roll lightly. Cover the bottom of Dutch oven or roasting pan with some of the cabbage leaves. Arrange the cabbage rolls in layers in pan. Pour the tomato juice over the cabbage rolls and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook meat and onions; season with spices. Pour salsa in a shallow dish. Dip a tortilla in salsa, coating both sides. Lay in a plate and add your meat in the center. Sprinkle with cheese if you'd like. Roll and place in a 9 x 13 baking dish, seam side down.

Repeat until all tortillas are used. Pour leftover salsa on top of enchiladas and sprinkle with more cheese. If you have any meat leftover, you can mix it with the sauce and pour over tortillas. Bake at 350° until heated thoroughly and cheese is melted.

title: spinach-beet salad
directions: Rinse, drain and dry spinach.
Tear enough spinach into pieces to yield 2 quarts.
Pour French dressing over julienne beets; chill.
When ready to serve, add marinated beets and herb croutons to spinach.
Gently turn and toss until greens are evenly coated with dressing.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg slices.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Mix the pineapple, sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add the cheese.
Place in buttered Pyrex dish.
Melt the margarine. Crumble the crackers in the melted margarine and sprinkle on top of the pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 20 minutes).

title: spanish spaghetti
directions: Saute onion until lightly browned.
Stir in chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer for about 20 minutes, stirring often.
Layer spaghetti and cheese in casserole, saving 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour sauce over top and sprinkle olives over sauce.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cheesy bacon bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, bacon, onions and pepper in bowl.
Separate crescent rolls into 2 triangles.
Pinch seams together.
Spread cheese mixture on each triangle.
Roll up, starting at longest side, and seal.
Cut each roll into 16 slices. Place slices, cut side down, on flat cookie sheet, greased.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yields 32 appetizers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pick chicken from bones.
Boil the egg noodles in chicken broth from chicken.
Mix all other ingredients with chicken and egg noodles.

title: baked soy drumsticks
directions: In a large shallow roasting pan, stir together the broth, soy sauce, oil, oregano and ginger.
Add drumsticks in a single layer. Bake in a preheated oven at 425°, basting occasionally, for 40 minutes, or until well browned and tender.
Serve hot or cold. Makes 20 servings (2 drumsticks each).

title: pineapple cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan, and bake at 350° until done (about 40 minutes).
When cool frost with icing.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and retain only pineapple juice. Add orange powder and instant
pudding	to
pineapple
juice. Stir until smooth.
Fold in fruit and chill.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Let stand for 1 to 2 hours. Put in jars and seal.
These are good to use the next day, and will keep in the refrigerator for months.
Yields 3 pints.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Melt butter over medium heat. Add onion and celery. Saute until soft. Add flour and stir 2 minutes.
Mix in broth.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until thickened.
(Stir occasionally.)
Mix in peanut butter and cream.
Transfer to blender and puree in small batches until smooth.
Heat to desired temperature and garnish with chives.

title: tacos
directions: Boil beef roast and pork roast about 3 hours with salt to taste.
Shred meat into small pieces.
Pour chili sauce, as much as needed to mix meat together.
In separate bowls, cut up lettuce, tomatoes, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Heat soft shells in microwave oven; fill with previous ingredients and taco sauce.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cube chicken breasts.
Dip into egg. Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Coat chicken in bread crumb combination.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a frying pan; lightly brown chicken cubes.
Remove from frying pan and put into broiler-safe pan.
Cube remaining butter, put in with chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil for 2 to 5 minutes, until lightly brown.
Serve with favorite pasta or baked potato.

title: texas delight
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and simmer in bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Boil noodles and drain.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Place on top of meat mixture and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° in a covered baking dish.

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix
oatmeal,
coconut,
nuts,	wheat
germ,
sunflower seeds, cinnamon and salt.	In separate bowl mix honey, vegetable
oil and
vanilla.
Pour over first mixture and mix well. Put
in
cake pans and bake at 300° for 25 minutes or lightly browned, stirring
every
10 to 15 minutes.	When cooled, you can add raisins or dates if desired.

title: grandma's tea cookies(from the files of adness williams crutchfield)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll out on floured board (very thin).
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° until brown, about 8 or 10 minutes.
Lemon or almond flavoring may be added instead of vanilla (1 teaspoon).

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of the cheese and croutons.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Bake 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add liquids in order given.
Flavor with vanilla.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for approximately 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: rice soy hot dish
directions: Brown meat; add all remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for last 15 minutes.
Entire baking time is 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican meatballs(serves 4)
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add egg gradually.
With floured hands and surface, work into meatballs (about 12 to 16). Pour about 3 tablespoons oil into a large frying pan, over high heat.
When oil is hot, fry meatballs about 5 to 10 minutes, or until brown, turning frequently.
Remove meatballs and let drain on paper towels.
Place in ovenproof dish and pour over the taco sauce.
Heat in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped onions and serve.

title: three-day bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and buttermilk; let stand until buttermilk is absorbed, about 3 minutes.
Beat in eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until flour is moistened.
Cover tightly and refrigerate up to 3 days.
(When you want hot muffins, bake as many as you need.)

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables (if still frozen, just cook longer in oven).
Mix vegetables, soup, sour cream, 1/2 can French fried onions and 3 ounces Swiss cheese.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1/2 hour or until bubbly hot.
Put remainder of Swiss cheese and French fried onions on top.
Put back in oven, uncovered, for 5 minutes to melt cheese and brown onions.
Serves 6.

title: sauce for indoor barbecue
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over chicken or pork.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter in bowl until creamy.
Gradually mix in powdered sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually.
Mix each item one at a time.
Grease pan lightly and place batter in tube pan as evenly as possible with spoon.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes; use toothpick to determine if cake is done.

title: italian sausage bake
directions: Crumble sausage; brown and drain.
With an electric mixer, whip eggs, cream and margarine together.
Add sausage and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour mixture into nonstick 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cover loosely with foil and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add syrup, oats, vanilla and salt. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes. Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Spread over slightly cooled baked mixture.

title: white cake
directions: Measure the cake flour and 1 1/4 cups sugar into a sifter. Measure the Crisco into mixer.
Measure the milk and vanilla or almond extract into a cup.
Have ready the 5 egg whites, beaten into meringue with 1/2 cup sugar.
(Beat egg whites until foamy. Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually until soft peaks are formed.)
Stir shortening just to soften.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk; mix until flour is dampened.
Beat 2 minutes.

title: granny's rolls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with an electric mixer.
Let this rest for 15 minutes.
Add oil and salt.
Add enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead for at least 5 minutes.
Let rise in a warm place for about 1 hour, covered.
After rising, punch down; knead a little and divide into 1-inch balls (have greased hands and pan ready).
Use a 7 x 11-inch size metal pan.
Let rise to double bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate and peanut butter squares
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, sugar, butter and peanut butter. Press into a 9 x 13 pan. Melt chocolate chips and spread over top. Chill at least 30 minutes and cut into squares.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Combine baking mix, milk and cheese, mixing lightly but thoroughly.
On floured surface, roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on baking sheet. Bake at 475° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Blend butter or margarine with garlic powder and brush on hot biscuits before removing from baking sheet.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Grate carrots and saute.
Add squash and saute.
Cook about 25 minutes.
Add dressing mix and sour cream. Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: purple cows
directions: Put 1 scoop of ice cream in a cup.
Pour grape juice over ice cream.
Ice cream will foam up to a very delicious drink!
Yum!

title: eggs piquant
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth; add cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts and mixture is thick and smooth (about five minutes).
Put two tablespoons of mixture in the bottom of six custard cups.
Break an egg into each cup.
Add another two tablespoons of mixture on top of each.
Place in shallow pan containing one inch of hot water. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
A delicious recipe from Wilma Green.

title: milk lefse
directions: Bring to a boil in 2-quart saucepan all ingredients except flour.
Pour this boiling mixture into flour.
Stir and roll. Makes 10 large rounds.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Melt margarine in shallow baking dish.
Stir in pecans to coat with margarine.
Roast in oven at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Taste test after 20 to 25 minutes. Roast to the toastiness that you desire.
When done, drain on paper towels.
Salt to taste while warm.

title: plum pudding
directions: Combine the mincemeat, bread crumbs, plums, salt and spices in a mixing bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add milk. Add this to the dry mixture and stir well.
Add brandy and mix well.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart pudding mold.
Cover with a lid.
Place mold on a rack in a large pan, then add boiling water halfway up the side of the mold.
Cover the large pan with foil or a lid and steam over low heat for 4 hours.
Occasionally check water level to see if more needs to be added.
Cool, turning pudding out of mold.
Soak with brandy.

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; let cool.
Add sugar into cold water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add juices, ginger ale, sugar water and Jell-O mixture.
Freeze and serve slushy.

title: golden punch
directions: Heat the sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Mix the remaining items and freeze until almost time to serve.
Can leave frozen up to 3 months. Remove 1 hour before serving; thaw and add ginger ale or club soda.
Can use Rocky Top's lemon/lime soda. This recipe serves 100.
I freeze in gallon Ziploc baggies so they will lay flat in freezer.
I use 2-liter bottles to 1 gallon bag, or to your personal taste.

title: savory beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery in butter.
Put cooked noodles and meat mixture in a casserole.
Stir lightly.
Bake for 1 hour. Add olives the last 10 minutes (optional).
I 4 times the recipe for 35 people.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, except Ritz. Sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs all over top. Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes or until broccoli is done.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle on meat on both sides.
Brown meat well on both sides in Dutch oven.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Stir well.
Simmer, covered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until meat is good and tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mold into small balls and freeze. To cook, place frozen balls on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Do not crowd cookie sheet, it will lengthen cooking time. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter graham fudge
directions: Stir together all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Put in an oblong 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour on top of mixture.
Let cool.

title: baked spaghetti(reduced fat)
directions: Saute beef, onion, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper until brown.
Pour off fat.
Stir in undrained mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Coat 8-inch deep casserole dish with nonstick vegetable coating spray.
Place half of cooked spaghetti in bottom of dish.
Layer half of meat mixture on spaghetti.

title: creole style beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion and green pepper to all drippings; cook until tender.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes; cook until thickened.
Add beans.
Top with bacon.
Heat at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chantilly potatoes
directions: In mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat potatoes, milk and butter until smooth.
Blend in salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with whipped cream and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: brownies
directions: In mixing bowl, beat sugar and butter; add eggs and mix well. Add flour, cocoa and salt.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until set.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put peanuts, sugar, Karo and salt in microwavable bowl and microwave for 10 to 11 minutes on High.
Remove bowl and add vanilla and butter until melted.
Add soda; stir vigorously until it turns golden color.
Pour on greased cookie sheet and cool. Break into pieces.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, sour cream, 1/2 cup cheese, pepper and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Add soups and water, enough for cooking.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Spoon over toasted bread or buns.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: dian's taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients and serve.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and margarine until blended. Add remaining ingredients; mix and mold into ball.

title: country fried mullet fish
directions: In fish fryer or deep boiler, bring to a boil enough oil to freely float fish.
Roll fish portions in corn meal until well covered.
Place into oil along with salt pork.
Cook until fish floats to top and can easily be forked.
Do not remove the bacon until all fish portions are done.
Serve crisp bacon slices with the fish.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot tomato juice.
Add other ingredients and pour into molds.
Chill several hours until set.
Serve with a bit of Miracle Whip and an olive or two to decorate.

title: venison jerky
directions: Trim all fat from meat; cut into very thin strips.
Mix and soak overnight.
Arrange strips on cookie sheet.
Set oven at 200°.
Leave oven door cracked to let moisture escape (put a spoon in the door).
Bake 4 to 7 hours.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef, salt to taste and drain.
Add all ingredients except the corn bread, simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Make cornbread according to package directions.
Pour meat mixture into square pan.
Dollop cornbread mixture on top of meat.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix rest of ingredients with onions and simmer on low for 10 minutes.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Using mallet, pound chicken pieces to about 1/4-inch thickness and set aside.
Put some sauce in bottom of 6 x 10-inch baking pan.
Spoon Ricotta onto centers of breasts and roll jellyroll fashion.
Arrange chicken rolls, seam side down.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Top with Mozzarella and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until tender.

title: no-bake layered dessert
directions: Dip each cookie in the bowl of milk; arrange cookies in a single layer in a serving dish.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip over cookies; alternate layers, ending with Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: kahlua
directions: Thoroughly clean 2 medium sized glass bottles (preferably made of brown glass).
Combine coffee, sugar and water.
Heat until sugar is combined with other ingredients.
Pour in whiskey and stir.
Put 1/2 of the vanilla bean in each bottle.
Add the cooled Kahlua and seal.
Let stand in a cool, dark place for at least 30 days.

title: cheese broccoli cornbread
directions: Make cornbread according to directions.
Add chopped broccoli and grated cheese.
Bake until done.
Almost a meal in itself.

title: walnut squash cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine wet ingredients; mix well.
Add squash and walnuts.
Combine with dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan until knife comes out clean.
Top with cream cheese frosting.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, melted butter and soda, dissolved in hot water.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Shape into small balls. Place on baking sheet and press down.
Cookies will be soft at first, but will be harder when cool.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: peanut butter cups(makes 28 cups)
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients (filling).
Melt chocolate bits and Crisco in microwave for 2 minutes.
Drop chocolate mixture in bottom of small cupcake tins.
Put 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter mixture in each cup.
Put in refrigerator.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Line a 10 x 12-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Place cooked beef on top of tortillas.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Add beans, then cheese.
Break up remaining tortillas and place on top.
Mix tomatoes and green chilies and cream of chicken soup and pour over the casserole.
Sprinkle top with chopped chilies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: sparkling gingersnaps(ruth's)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Add all dry ingredients; mix well. Blend in raisins. Chill if desired for easier handling.
Shape into balls and dip in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, sugar side up. Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Great!

title: mushroom soup
directions: In a large saucepan combine chicken broth and wild rice. Bring to boil; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until rice is cooked.
Whisk flour and thyme into cream; add to broth and rice stirring constantly and heat until thickened.
Meanwhile, melt butter in skillet and saute mushrooms and onions for about 5 minutes; add to soup mixture.
Cook a few minutes more until hot but not boiling.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift corn meal and salt together; pour boiling water over, stirring quickly.
Add milk quickly to prevent lumping.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in baking powder and butter.
Pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and syrup together.
Add milk and well beaten eggs, then add pineapple and coconut.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, but not brown, 10 to 12 minutes, at 375°.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll again in powdered sugar.

title: mushroom rolls
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Cool and add flour. Blend well and add salt.
Stir in cream and blend.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice and chives.
Cool. Roll slices of bread flat and spread mixture on bread as for jelly roll.
Freeze lightly, then cut into thirds.
Dip in melted butter and crushed cornflake crumbs.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400° until light brown.

title: vegetable sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a heavy glass jar.
Set in a pan of hot water and turn the heat on low.
Stir until well blended and heated through.
Refrigerate; reheat and use as needed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in large bowl in order listed. Cover tightly and refrigerate over night or several hours. Toss just before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until it starts to get thick.
Stir often.
Remove from heat.
Mix with mixer until creamy.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: swedish sylta
directions: Cook all together until meat is well done.
Cool and either grind or tear into small pieces.
Put into loaf pan and cover with meat broth.
Cool overnight before slicing (the gelatin in meat bones thickens juice).
Serve cold; nice for buffets.

title: 14 layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix as any layer cake.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Use iron griddle sprayed with Pam.
(I use Crisco).
Add 4 large tablespoons batter for first 2 layers.
Then start using 3 to 3 1/2 spoons for other layers.
Bake 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or lightly brown.
Stake cake and ice as each layer is done.

title: strawberry shakes(makes two 1-cup servings)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and whip.

title: cinnamon applesauce loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine first 4 ingredients. In a large bowl, blend applesauce, sugar, Egg Beaters and margarine. Stir in flour mixture just until blended. Batter will be lumpy.
Mix in raisins.
Spoon batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy caramel pullaways
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter or margarine, sugars, egg and vanilla in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Stir flour, baking soda and salt together.
Beat into butter and sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix with hands (will be stiff).
Roll in small ball.
Press in nut half or press down with fork dipped in flour.
Bake 20 or 25 minutes on ungreased tin at 350°.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: nanny's potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in chicken broth.
When potatoes are soft, reduce heat to low and add butter, half and half and parsley. Cook and drain summer sausage; add to soup.
Serve with green salad and crusty, hot French bread.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend at high speed in blender.

title: candied pickles
directions: Mix garlic through pickles in crock or container.
Add sugar. Pour over pickles.
Do not stir until 2 days later, then stir each day for 7 days.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Add potato, celery, onion, salt, pepper, thyme and liquid from clams.
Heat to boil.
Cook, covered 10 minutes.
Combine flour and milk.
Add to mixture. After thickening, add clams.
Heat through.
Do not boil.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: hip and thigh cake
directions: Make cake as directed.
While cake is hot, punch holes into cake.
Mix Eagle Brand milk with caramel topping and pour over hot cake. After cake cools, put Cool Whip on top.
Crumble Butterfinger candy bars and sprinkle over top.

title: parmesan potato soup
directions: In a large soup kettle, saute onion in butter until tender. In a separate bowl, mix flour and seasonings.
Stir into onion. Gradually add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots, bacon and milk.
Simmer on low heat until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Add cheese. Stir well and heat through.
Enjoy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix and melted oleo.
Put 1/2 of mixture into buttered casserole dish.
Pour in squash, onion and carrots.
Mix soup and sour cream together, then add to other mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Melt butter; add to crumbs and mix well.
Arrange in baking dish in layers the squash mixture and crumbs.
End with crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pound cake 1
directions: Cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Let cool before taking out of pan.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.
Pour rest of milk and pudding mix into bowl.
Beat with whisk for about 2 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and cinnamon.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cheese.
Pour drained pineapple on bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese mixture over pineapple. Top with Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle butter evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Using a fork, cream together cheeses, salt and sugar. Dissolve soaked gelatin over hot water.
Stir quickly into the cheeses.
Add chopped nuts, diced pepper and chopped olives, reserving about six for garnish.
Have a five cup ring mold well oiled with Wesson Oil.
Arrange garnish (olives and pecans or pepper) in the bottom of the mold.
Press cheese mixture into mold.
Refrigerate, unmold and serve with "Cousin Melvina's Dressing".

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Slice the mushrooms and place in a glass bowl.
In a saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over mushrooms.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 5 hours.

title: quick salisbury steak
directions: Make 6 patties, dip in egg, then in flour or bread crumbs. Brown patties in 1 tablespoon oil.
Season with salt and pepper. Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: steve's deep fried fish(quebec style)
directions: Combine ingredients, except fillets and mix well.
Keep fillets cut 1 1/2 to 3 1/2-inches thick and batter cold so fish won't soak up too much oil.
Use peanut oil at 350° to 375°; a candy thermometer works well to maintain temperature.
Too many fillets deep fried together will cause fish to stick together and temperature will drop below 350° resulting in soggy fish.
Keep fish in oil until golden brown and place on wire rack over paper towel lined plate for crispness.
Use leftover batter and dribble in hot oil to make delicious crunchies that everyone will love. When done, strain oil through cheesecloth so you can use it several times.
Place potato slice in hot oil to remove all flavors.
This recipe works great with walleye, Northern pike or crappie.

title: candy sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until done.
Slice and butter.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour it over sweet potatoes. Cook 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
If desired, tie whole spices in cheesecloth.
(If spices are loose, strain before serving.)
Cover and set on low for 2 to 8 hours.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and gradually beat in 2 well-beaten eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Beat in 1 cup salad dressing.
Pour cooked dressing over potatoes, eggs, cucumber and onion.
Stir; add additional salt and pepper, if desired.

title: caitlin's favorite blueberry pancakes
directions: Empty can of blueberries from package mix into strainer. Wash under cold running water. Drain. Blend muffin mix, flour and baking powder with a fork. Stir in slightly beaten egg, water and oil. Mix until well blended. Stir in blueberries. Cook on griddle until golden brown.

title: quick mashed squash
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Simmer on low until liquid is gone.
Mash squash well and serve warm.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Set aside 1 package of chopped beef.
Cream together remaining ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Cover the cheese ball with the remaining chopped beef.
Serve with carrot sticks, celery sticks and crackers.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: andes mint cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, combine butter, sugar and water. Heat until butter melts; add chocolate chips. Stir until partially melted. Remove from heat and continue to stir until totally melted. Pour into large mixing bowl and cool 10 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In large bowl, mix ingredients. Stir together. Dish out into small bowls. Chill and serve cold.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into balls. Roll balls in flour. Brown in a skillet with a small amount of Crisco.
Place browned meat balls in a dish and cover with mushroom soup.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tossed salad(method:  fireless)
directions: Wash all vegetables.
Tear apart lettuce; place into a clean, doubled 4-gallon plastic garbage bag.
Chop tomatoes, carrots, celery, cucumbers and green peppers.
Add to lettuce.
Pour in sunflower seeds and salad dressing.
Seal bag with twist tie, and play catch.
Serve salad from bag.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop in small balls.
Bake at 200° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely; roll in powdered sugar again.

title: creme de la creme
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, mix gelatine and sugar.
Stir in heavy cream; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir over low heat until dissolved (5 to 10 minutes).
Remove from heat; cool in refrigerator (20 to 30 minutes).
Fold in vanilla and sour cream until smooth.
Pour into mold; let set several hours or overnight.

title: hot dog meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion and eggs; mix well. Place half of the mixture in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Top with cheese and hot dogs.
Top with rest of the beef.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a large pot, brown meat in olive oil.
Add all ingredients, except sour cream.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Check occasionally and add water, if necessary.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: moon pie
directions: Bring water to a boil until margarine melts.
Add flour and eggs.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Will be thick.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring batter up on sides of pan to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Fry pork chops in small amount of oil; place in casserole dish. Mix soup, 1 can water and chopped peppers; pour over pork chops. Sprinkle rice over this and press into soup.
Bake at 350° until rice is done.
Cover with cheese.
When cheese is melted, remove from oven and serve.

title: sausage toasties
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef and drain.
Mix both with garlic powder and oregano.
Melt cheese and stir into meat mixture. Spread onto rye party bread and freeze.
Toast (heat) as needed.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Crush cookies and divide in half.
Place half of the cookies in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Combine the two mixtures, then stir in the Cool Whip.
Pour the mixture over the cookies in the dish.
Smooth and sprinkle the top with remaining cookies.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicago dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
To assemble, place hot dogs in buns; spread mustard over the hot dog and add chopped onion and relish and top with two tomato wedges per dog.
Wrap each hot dog, individually, in foil and place in a warm oven about 10 minutes until heated through to simulate the Chicago carts featuring steamed hot dogs dressed in this way.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Boil chicken in large pot with plenty of water for broth.
Let meat get boiling real good.
Turn down low.
Add onions and celery.
When chicken is done, dip meat out of broth and let cool. Pick meat off of the bones.
Return to broth.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes more.
Cool and serve.

title: grandpa walton's pecan-pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add corn syrup, sugar, oleo, pumpkin and vanilla. Beat well. Arrange pecans on bottom of pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Butter 7 x 11-inch pan.
Mix together broccoli, onion, salt, cheese, eggs and Jiffy corn meal mix.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Thaw strawberries, slice bananas and mix with pie filling and strawberries.

title: mama's chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken until tender; take out of stock and cut into chunks, then place back into stock.
Add all other ingredients; cook until onion and vegetables are tender.
Serve with hot rolls.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water and bring to a boil.
Mix next four ingredients; add water if necessary.
Add to raisins and boil until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix cauliflower, broccoli, onion and Mozzarella cheese together.
Set aside.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Mix chicken with softened cream cheese, salt, pepper and onion salt.
Add milk.
Divide rolls into triangles; fill with mixture. Fold top over to form squares.
Brush with butter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: white chili
directions: In a large pot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion; saute until brown.
Add next 7 ingredients; stir until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush entire package of oreos into small crumbs.
Save 1/4 cup to be used later.
Spread cookie crumbs in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with cookie crumbs.
Stir well and flatten mixture with fork.
Chill.

title: homemade ice cream(for one gallon freezer)
directions: Beat eggs, then add all other ingredients.
Put into freezer can.
Add about 2-inches ice around the can while freezer is turning, then about 1/3 cup rock salt (or ice cream salt). Continue alternating ice and salt, covering the lid evenly.
As ice melts down, add more ice and salt.
Set freezer in sink or tub as excess water will drain out of the hole in the side.
As soon as motor begins to strain, unplug it so you don't burn out the motor; takes 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Combine.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: deer sauce picante
directions: Cube deer meat into 1-inch pieces.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put meat into a large Ziploc bag to marinate for 2 hours in icebox.
Brown meat and sausage; remove and drain off the fat. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in meat and enough water to cover meat, adding steak sauce, tomato sauce and Ro-Tel.
Cover and cook for 2 hours.
Season to taste. Add parsley 30 minutes before serving.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Saute bacon with seasonings.
Add tomatoes, peas and consomme.
Simmer 30-45 minutes.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic salt and hot sauce.
This makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: country corn salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a 2-quart serving dish. In a saucepan, combine the vinegar and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and add sugar substitute.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13 inch pan. Beat remaining ingredients and pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 35 - 45 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: whole wheat batter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add whole wheat flour, salt, most of butter, honey and molasses.
Beat well.
Stir in white flour. Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Punch down.
Reserve 1/2 cup batter.
Spoon remaining batter into 16 muffin tins.
Spoon 1 teaspoon of reserved batter on top of each roll.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Brush tops lightly with butter.

title: bird cake
directions: Sift all together in large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Make a well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix with a spoon (don't use a beater) until well blended.
Pour in a tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes and turn out.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Boil water.
Add rice and let set.
Brown sausage, onion and bell pepper in frying pan.
Drain grease on paper towels set into colander.
In medium bowl, mix eggs, soup, milk and cheese.
Add sausage mixture and rice.
Bake in casserole dish for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream muffins
directions: Soften ice cream and mix with flour.
Spoon into muffin cups, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add beaten egg and extract.
Add potato buds and biscuit mix and mix well.
Form into balls (or drops) and bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Very good!

title: caramel ice cream
directions: Heat 1 cup milk.
Melt 1 cup sugar until light brown color. Add hot milk and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Beat the eggs; add remaining milk, sugar and salt.
Add to cooked mixture and cook until eggs are done.
Cool mixture; add vanilla and thick cream.
Finish filling can with milk or cream.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: red beet salad
directions: Three hours before ready to eat:
Pickle red beets and hard-boiled eggs in vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and small amount of water to almost cover eggs.
Cover dish and put in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Stir now and then to make eggs red.
(Use most of juice from red beets with vinegar.)

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar.
Mix in the flour, then the shortening.
Put in refrigerator.
Pinch off and use as needed.
These do not have to rise before baking, but be sure your yeast is fresh.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Form into a ball.
May be rolled in chopped nuts.

title: calico bacon bean casserole
directions: Break bacon into pieces.
Cook hamburger and onions until hamburger is browned.
Drain and rinse under hot water.
Drain all cans of beans.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and salt.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Stem and wash mushrooms; soak in salt water.
Butter casserole dish; place mushrooms in casserole dish, holes up.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Pare and slice eggplant 1/2-inch thick.
Dip each slice in well beaten eggs. Coat with very fine cracker meal or bread crumbs.
Place oil in frying pan to moderate heat.
Place eggplant slices, brown on both sides.
In baking dish, place eggplant. Cover with Mozzarella cheese and cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: randall's zesty beans
directions: Stir together all ingredients in a pot.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. 10-12 servings.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook onion in small amount of oil until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Heat and stir.
Add meat and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Cook eggplant and drain good.
Then mash.
Add egg and soda cracker crumbs, enough to hold eggplant together firm.
Fry sausage meat done and drain all the grease off and stir into eggplant.
Make into patties and fry.

title: coconut easter eggs
directions: Mix potatoes and butter together well (by hands).
Add vanilla.
Add the sugar gradually.
Mix well.
Add coconut.
This makes 9 or 10 eggs which weigh 1/4 pound.

title: sparkling punch
directions: This base can be made ahead and the pop added when ready to use.

title: pumpkin squase
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Mix 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Mix all other ingredients together. Pour into bowl over butter; do not mix.
Sprinkle with reserved sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover bottom with bacon strips.
Pour uncooked rice over bacon.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix soup with milk and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with seasoning from rice. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat.
Drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300° to 325°.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
Cool

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Squeeze to remove water (very important).
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients; mix well. Shape into 3/4 to 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, drain and squeeze.
Mix the ingredients together and put into the refrigerator for one hour.
Roll into balls about bite-sized and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa krispie balls
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter until well blended. Add Cocoa Krispies; mix until well coated.
Roll balls to coat in extra sugar or coconut.
Place on cookie sheet and cool until firm.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Add vanilla, sour cream, egg and apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: my secret brownie recipe
directions: In microwave, melt chocolate squares for 5 minutes on Defrost. In medium bowl, beat the eggs.
Add the margarine and sugar and beat it again (pretend it's someone you don't like).
Add flour, salt and vanilla and beat it again!
Add nuts until you can hardly stir batter.
Hire help if you want more nuts.

title: kale soup
directions: Simmer soup bones, onion, salt and garlic in water for about 2 hours.
Slice linguica into "coins."
Add to soup pot and simmer another half hour.
Add kale, potatoes and beans.
Continue to simmer until potatoes are tender (about 20 minutes).
Remove bones.
Can be cooled so fat can be removed.
Even better, let soup mellow for a day before serving.

title: chicken chow mein, american-style
directions: Brown onion lightly in margarine.
Add next 4 ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend and stir into meat mixture; add cornstarch mixed in cold water.
Cook until slightly thickened and clear.
Serve hot on chow mein noodles.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in a deep plastic bowl with a lid.
Pour pineapple juice over the chicken breasts.
Add chopped garlic and 1/2 bottle of soy sauce.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Delicious when grilled!
Serves 6.

title: *corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot water.
Set aside to cool.
Mix celery, corned beef, onion, eggs and green pepper with the Miracle Whip.
Add to jello.
Set in the refrigerator overnight in a greased bread loaf pan.

title: fast topping
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Then beat with other ingredients until stiff.
Spread over cold cake and sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain. Cook rice in water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Combine rice, broccoli, sugar and celery.
Saute onion in margarine; add to broccoli and rice mixture.
Stir in 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and mushroom soup.
Add 3/4 cup of grated cheese.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish with 1/2 tablespoon butter.
Arrange half the potatoes in an even layer on the bottom of the dish.
Cover with half the apples.
Sprinkle with half the brown sugar; dot with half the remaining butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Bake covered for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and baste with juices in dish.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes longer; baste again and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bobbie's cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Great with cream soup or alone.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Brown hamburger meat with oregano and garlic salt to taste. Place tortillas in 4 dinner plates.
Spoon hamburger meat over tortillas, layer salsa, onion, or any additional toppings, i.e. ripe olives, mushrooms, etc.
Top with shredded cheese and place in microwave oven until cheese melts.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Let lemonade thaw; mix lemonade, Cool Whip and milk until smooth.
Pour in pie crust.
Put in icebox and let set for 2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: black forest pie
directions: Crush Oreos; mix with melted butter and then divide into 2 pie pans.
Set aside.

title: mini biscuits
directions: Use mini cupcake pan.
Mix and cook in greased mini muffin pan.

title: barbecued n-a-d  oven cheesecake
directions: Set cream cheese out to soften.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar to beaten egg whites.
Gradually add cream cheese until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 275° for 25 minutes.
Let stand until cool, then refrigerate.
Top as desired (strawberries, cherries, etc.).
To make whipped topping, whip cream until stiff (do not overwhip).
Add sugar and vanilla.

title: easy congealed salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple.
Add jello, then cool real good (you might stick in the refrigerator).
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
May be topped with nuts, if desired.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Melt and cool chocolate pieces.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt to batter and beat on high speed for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat 3 minutes after each egg is added.
Carefully fold in chocolate quickly. Pour in pie shell and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet treats
directions: Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix milk with dry bread crumbs, then mix all ingredients (except chili sauce and jelly) together.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Brown meatballs in skillet or oven.
Heat chili sauce and jelly in a pan.
Add browned meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: honey glazed turkey
directions: Heat honey, sherry and butter in a saucepan.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and salt.
Pour honey mixture over turkey breast and let stand, covered in refrigerator for 3 to 5 hours.
Place turkey breast on smoker grid and baste.
Baste once again when almost done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Put into a greased casserole.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise and spread over vegetables.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german casserole
directions: Pour sauerkraut into casserole dish and sprinkle with rice. Add onion, meat, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix well.
It is better if it sets overnight.

title: k~f~c cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots. Mix balance of ingredients well. Pour over cabbage and carrots. Chill.

title: economy oven dish
directions: Layer into buttered casserole in order given, the first 5 ingredients.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Brown hamburger.
Place on top of vegetables in casserole.
Cover with tomato soup in which sugar and oregano have been mixed.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: better rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions using chicken broth instead of water.
In small saucepan, saute onion and shrimp in butter. Combine with cooked rice and serve.
Makes 2 side dishes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add pineapple, green pepper, 1 cup nuts, onion and seasoned salt. Chill well, then form mixture into a ball. Roll cheese ball in remaining pecan pieces.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, oleo, vanilla, pineapple and eggs.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake 1 hour in a 300° oven.
This pie freezes well after baking.

title: yummy bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until soft.
Press in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: dream pie(2 pies)
directions: Heat cherries and pineapple.
Add sugar mixture and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add dry jello.
Let cool 30 minutes. Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into crusts (any kind is great), preferably graham cracker.
Cool and keep in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, oats, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and hot pepper sauce.
Add 1/4 cup water and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Sift flour once and then measure and mix with soda, baking powder and salt.
Sift again.
Cream shortening and add sugar gradually, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add vanilla and then well beaten eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with sour milk.
Mix cocoa and hot water to form a smooth paste.
Beat into batter and pour into 3 small or 2 large layer cake pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons into batter.
Cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect.
Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips if desired.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: While broccoli is cooking, saute onions in margarine.
Add soup and milk to onions, then add Cheez Whiz.
Simmer 1 minute. Add broccoli, rice and seasonings.
Bake in a greased casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: On a large platter, make a layer of each ingredient.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with the salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in 3 1/2-quart slow cooker.
Mix water and soup until well blended.
(You may add sour cream and flour mixture now if you will be cooking on low temperature.) Pour liquid over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
(Or cook on high for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, adding sour cream and flour mixture during last 30 minutes.)
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Bake in glass pan (9 x 13-inch).
While cake is still warm, make slits in cake and pour the Eagle Brand milk on top.
After cake is cool, ice with Cool Whip and serve.

title: royal marble cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler. Combine 3/4 cup flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cut in butter until fine particles.
Stir in 2 tablespoons melted chocolate.
Press into spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chile relleno bake
directions: Combine cheeses; spread half on bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan. Split open chiles and place over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Gradually add milk to flour.
Blend well.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with your favorite pastry.
Peel peaches and place in unbaked pie shell cavity side down.
Cream together 1 cup of sugar and 1/3 cup of butter.
Into this mixture, put 1/3 cup of flour, then add beaten egg and vanilla.
Spread this mixture over top of peaches and bake in slow oven for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Let cream cheese and butter or margarine sit out and soften several hours before making cake.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar together; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after adding each one.
Add cake flour.
Beat well after adding cake flour.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Beat well.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325° or 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: "philly" brunch quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cheese and milk in saucepan and stir over low heat until smooth.
Gradually add cream cheese mixture to eggs; mix until well blended.
Saute onion in margarine. Add onion and remaining ingredients to mixture; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until set. Excellent served with fresh fruit and hot rolls.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until almost done (add salt and pepper to taste). Roll can biscuits into small balls, drop into chicken.
When dumplings are almost done, add cream of chicken or mushroom soup. Cook on medium to medium-low heat until dumplings are completely done.
Stir gently as to not tear chicken off bone.
If too thick, add water as needed.

title: hot dog surprise
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite-size pieces.
Put in frying pan with remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly for 40 minutes.
Sauce should be consistency of thick catsup.
If liquid dries too much, add more bourbon.

title: pecan pies
directions: Beat
eggs
slightly.
Beat
in
by hand, sugar, syrup, melted margarine, salt, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: aunt nell's dessert
directions: Cook jello, pineapple with juice and marshmallows until thickens; cool.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Mix and add to jello mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: rhubarb custard pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Mix these 3 ingredients together, then add 2 cups chopped rhubarb. Pour into pie pan. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: souffled carrots
directions: Peel carrots and slice into thin rings.
Boil until tender; drain and mash well.
Add oleo, sugar and egg.
Add milk, flour, cinnamon and baking powder and blend.

title: red lobster rolls
directions: Combine baking mix, milk and cheese and mix with wooden spoon until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop dough by heaping tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Combine butter with garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: golden squares
directions: Combine and put in a 9 x 9 pan.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy chili mac
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in slow cooker pot over medium heat on top of range.
Remove excess grease.
Add tomatoes, beans, tomato paste, water, chili powder, season salt, cumin and pepper.
Stir to combine and break tomatoes.
Cover crock-pot and slow cook on heating base at setting number 3 for 6 to 8 hours.
Twenty minutes before serving, cook Creamettes according to directions on package.
Drain and stir into chili.
Cover and cook 10 more minutes.
Garnish with cheese per serving.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: chocolated-cheese cups
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend on high until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine egg whites and salt in a medium bowl; beat at medium speed until stiff peaks form.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Coat paper muffin pan liners with cooking spray; sprinkle evenly with graham cracker crumbs.
Spoon batter into liners, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 225° for 30 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, sprinkle with almonds.
Yield:
16 (63 calories each).

title: apple butter bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, and cinnamon; set aside Combine eggs, butter and raisins. Add flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until wooded pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove to wire rack, and cool completely.

title: souper stew
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients (except noodles) in Dutch oven or 3 or 4-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 3 hours adding small amount of water if mixture becomes too thick. Serve on bed of noodles.

title: albacore tuna tortellini salad
directions: Prepare tortellini according to directions; drain and cool.
Stir in drained tuna, peas, Ranch dressing and olives.

title: microwave mexican dip
directions: Mix together.
Microwave on High 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Mix together and pour over top 1/2 can tomato juice.
Seal casserole tightly with heavy foil.
Bake in 250° oven for 4 hours. Can be cooked in a crock-pot also.

title: hot meat dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain fat from it.
Next, in a large bowl, mix cream cheese until blended well with spoon.
Then add Pace picante sauce.
Serve hot.
Makes enough servings for a party of 30 people.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Mix ketchup, mustard, onion, water and bouillon together in a large bowl.
Pour over meat; simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Cook noodles as directed.
Pour meat mixture over noodles.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil and boil, stirring continually until sugar is dissolved.
Very slowly, add sugar syrup to 2 unbeaten egg whites in mixing bowl, beating continually with electric mixer until stiff peaks form, about 7 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
In large pot, combine hamburger and onion and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil. Sprinkle rice or barley over top and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain grease; add taco seasoning mix. Let cook into the meat for a few minutes.
In another pan, heat enchilada sauce.
Dip tortillas in sauce and place in a round casserole dish; spoon meat on tortillas and chopped olives and cheese.
Then repeat:
tortilla, meat, olives and cheese.
The last layer should show just the meat and cheese.
Pour any leftover sauce over the top.
Bake at 350° until hot.
I think about 45 minutes.
You can also add chopped chilies, if you desire.

title: thunder and lightening
directions: Mix together oil, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Dice and mix vegetables.
Pour oil and vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Mix and serve with peas, beans, potatoes, etc.

title: sheila's beef and macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: veggie melts
directions: Combine carrot, zucchini, mushrooms, onions, green pepper, cheese, salt and salad dressing.
Mix thoroughly.
Place a rounded teaspoonful of vegetable mixture on each toast round.
Place on microwave-safe plate.
Microwave on High until cheese melts. Watch closely.
Makes 24.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Beat evaporated milk until soft peaks form; fold in marshmallows.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Combine cranberry mixture, marshmallow mixture, pineapple and pecans in a large bowl.
Stir gently until well mixed.
Cover salad and chill. Yields 12 servings.

title: nancy's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
When cool, shred chicken.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a casserole dish.
Place leftover crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until brown on top and sides.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Peel eggs and cut in slices.
Toss to mix well.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook potatoes in water to cover until tender.
Peel.
Slice into baking dish.
Blend sugars and flour.
Stir in water; add butter, vanilla and nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bring to a boil in saucepan.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting with syrup.

title: crinkle cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar and roll.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry fresh pie
directions: Combine pudding mix, gelatin, water and lemon juice in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour into a bowl and chill until thickened.
Fold in half of whipped topping, blending well.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into pie shell and chill until set, 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping and more strawberries.
