title: lemon chiffon cheesecake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, and graham cracker crumbs. Put 2/3 in bottom of 9 x 13 dish. Mix jello and hot water; let cool. Cream sugar, cream cheese, and lemon juice. Mix jello and cream cheese mixture; add whip cream. Blend lightly and pour into crust. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.

title: fried olives
directions: Coat the olive with egg and flour.
Fry them using plenty of hot oil until golden brown.
Drain them on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Serves 4.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions and set aside.
Mix first three ingredients and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, margarine and nuts.

Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Let cool and crumble in same pan and spread evenly over bottom. Fold Dream Whip into cheese mixture and spread on crumbled crust. Put pie filling over this and chill.

title: continental chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef on bottom of a greased cooker. Wrap each piece of boned chicken with a strip of bacon and lay on top of the dried beef.
Mix the soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours (high for 3 to 4 hours). Serve over a bed of steamed rice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple. Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Brown beef in oil with onions, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper; cook 1 1/2 hours.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese and spinach.
Layer in a sprayed lasagne pan the noodles, sauce, Mozzarella-cottage cheese mixture, noodles, cottage cheese mixture, Mozzarella, sauce and Parmesan cheese.

title: punch(20 cups)
directions: Boil water and add the tea bags.
While still warm, add sugar, then set aside to cool.
Combine mixed juices with tea.
When ready to serve pour over ice cubes in punch bowl, then add ginger ale and sparkling water.
If you would like the punch pink, use 1 quart of cranberry juice.
If you want colored ice cubes, put Kool-Aid in your ice trays.

title: adlai stevenson's cook's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Make white sauce with 4 1/2 tablespoons butter, flour, milk, cream, salt and pepper.
Arrange artichokes over the bottom of a buttered baking dish.
Scatter shrimp over the artichokes.
Cook the mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter for 6 minutes and spoon over shrimp-artichoke mixture.
Add sherry and Worcestershire sauce to white sauce and pour over contents of baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika and bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix together and chill 3 to 4 hours before rolling.
Roll into a log on Saran Wrap in pecan, parsley flake mixture.
Refrigerate overnight and serve with crackers.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Combine ingredients in large boiler and cook on medium heat until all the moisture is gone, about 15 minutes.
Peanuts will look pink frosted.
Be careful not to overcook and scorch. Pour peanuts into a large baking pan so peanuts will be in a single layer.
Cook in 300° oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
When cooked, store in airtight container or Ziploc bag.

title: wedding punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and stir.
Add cold water and fruit juices.
Pour into container and freeze.
One hour before, place in punch bowl and just before serving, add 7-Up. Mash, mix and drink.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together the soups, sour cream and butter.
Layer potatoes, onions, sauce and cheese; top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes, mixed with 4 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook and stir beef in oil in Dutch oven over medium heat until brown.
Stir in broth, pepper and salt; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Stir in water, carrots, potatoes, rutabaga and tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes until tender.

title: fat cake
directions: Slice bananas.
Drain juice off pineapple.
Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and bananas.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust, cover and cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: alyson's bran muffins
directions: Mix All-Bran, crushed Quaker rounds and boiling water.
Let cool.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate batter overnight.
Bake in regular muffin tins at 375° for 25 minutes or in small muffin tins for 20 minutes.
Use paper muffin tin liners.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Place mixture of first 6 ingredients in refrigerator.
Drain the vegetables.
Marinate vegetables with first mixture and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and pepper until brown.
Add all other ingredients except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: stan's hamburger noodle bake
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add tomato sauce, garlic, salt and sugar.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
While mixture is cooking mix cream cheese, sour cream, green onions and Cheddar cheese in a bowl. Combine cheese mixture with meat mixture and cooked noodles
and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and blend.
Add half of soda and salt to egg mixture and the rest in the mashed bananas.
Add bananas to eggs, then add flour.
Add milk and mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 325° until brown and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: stir-fry chicken with bacon and scallions
directions: Cut the bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut the chicken, across the grain, into 1/2-inch slices and toss it with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut the scallions, including the green tops, into thin slices.
Brown the bacon in a large frying pan.
Remove it from the pan.
Put half the chicken in the pan and sear over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, about 3 minutes.
Add to the cooked bacon and cook the remaining chicken in the same way.
Return the bacon and chicken to the pan and cook for 5 more minutes.
Add the wine or stock and stir in the scallions.
Taste for seasoning and add salt and pepper, if needed.
Serve with rice or buttered noodles.

title: red beans and brown rice
directions: Follow directions on package for soaking beans, either overnight or by quick-soak method.
Pour off water.
Cover beans with water, about 2 quarts.
Add ham bone and chopped onion. Simmer gently, covered, about 2 hours.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper, chili powder and sliced pepperoni (if desired). Continue to simmer gently, about 1 1/2 hours.
Follow directions on rice package.
Serve beans over rice.
Very good served with corn bread and a salad.
Serves 6.

title: easy cheese souffle
directions: Grate cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat egg yolks, salt, milk and flour together.
Add about 2/3 of cheese to egg yolk mixture, then very carefully fold egg whites into mixture.
Melt butter in an electric frypan until slightly brown. Pour in mixture.
Cover and cook for about 10 to 15 minutes at moderate temperature (I use 300°).
When souffle is golden brown and well risen, sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Serve with bread and butter immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook corn syrup, sugar and water to hard ball stage on candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites; add hot sugar mixture to egg whites by pouring into mixing bowl.
Do not stop beating until it loses its gloss.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased pan.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in beans, sauces, chili powder and garlic salt.
Heat to boil.
Place chips in baking dish (2-quart). Top with beef mixture.
Spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with onion, tomato and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Beat egg until light; add milk and cracklings.
Sift together flour, sugar, corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Add to the egg and milk mixture.
Beat well.
Turn into a flat baking pan and bake at 350° until nice and brown.

title: mushroom almond rice
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine until tender. Add rice and continue cooking until golden.
Add bouillon and pepper.
Stir well.
Heat to boiling.
Cover pan.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Saute almonds and mushrooms in remaining butter or margarine.
When rice is tender, add almonds and mushrooms and toss lightly.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix until smooth flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, salt, soda and milk.
Add poppy seed and nuts.
Beat well and mix 2 minutes.
Bake in angel food pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: egg drop noodle soup
directions: Place chicken stock in large saucepan and bring to a boil. Add noodles, boil for 5 minutes, or until noodles are just tender. Reduce heat to simmer.
Stir eggs, lemon juice, salt and pepper together well.
Slowly add eggs to stock in a thin stream, stirring gently with a fork.
Simmer for 1 minute, or until egg has set.
Sprinkle soup with chopped scallions, and serve hot.

title: nutty snack mix
directions: Put cereal and pecans in a cake pan.
Melt light corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine until boiling in the microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, depending on the microwave.
Mix all well together and bake at 250° for approximately 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces.
This is a good recipe for gift giving at the holidays.

title: stuffed chicken bread
directions: Add
poultry
seasoning,
garlic salt, black pepper and sage to taste.
If needed for liquid, use canned milk.

title: barbecue taco salads
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender and stir in barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese spread; stir until melted.
Arrange lettuce cups on platter.
Fill each cup with 1/2 cup shredded lettuce, 1/2 cup meat mixture, tomatoes and corn chips.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peggy's sausage biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk.
Add sausage, small amounts at a time. Roll and cut.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 40 small biscuits or 24 regular size biscuits.
For variety, add grated cheese to taste.

title: banana torte
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 5 tablespoons melted margarine and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dole pineapple berry smoothie
directions: Combine crushed pineapple, yogurt, banana, the berries and the ice cubes. Put into blender or food processor. Cover and blend until smooth.

title: susan's gourmet chicken casserole
directions: Skin breasts.
Place flat in greased 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and milk; pour over cheese. Mix stuffing and margarine.
Spread over soup.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cherry date squares
directions: Melt the shortening; blend with the brown sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder; add to the shortening and egg mixture.
Add the dates, cherries and nutmeats.
Spread the dough on a large cookie sheet. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes, or until dough is browned. Cool; cut into bars.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Mix together all juices with sugar until dissolved.
Add and stir in sherbet and ginger ale.
Serve in clear glass bowl.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix well the cornmeal, flour, baking soda, baking powder and sugar.
Add buttermilk and blend well.
Add shortening and blend. Add egg and blend.
Bake at 400° in lightly greased 8-inch cast-iron skillet until brown.

title: hash brown cheese potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together except 1/2 cup of butter, 1 cup of cheese and corn flakes.
Place the mixed ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place corn flakes and remaining cheese and butter on top for crust.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cover raisins with cold water and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine raisins, cherries, nuts and pineapple. Boil sugar and pineapple juice until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot syrup over egg whites. Add fruit, nuts and lemon juice. Blend in whipped cream.
Pour into a bread pan or into clean tin cans and freeze for at least 24 hours.

title: tuna with spaghetti
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in oil in a large frying pan. Mix in the tuna fish, tomato sauce, water, garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Pour tuna mixture over spaghetti.
Serves 6.

title: silly putty
directions: Here's a home remedy for bee stings:
wet the injured area and apply meat tenderizer.
It stops the pain immediately!

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and pecans and press into a
9-inch
or 2 (9-inch) pie pans
(mix
will
be
very sticky). Bake for 15 minutes at 325° until lightly brown. Let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on crust.
Mix puddings and milk and
spread over cream cheese layer.
Top
with
rest of
Cool
Whip.
Refrigerate. (Freezes well.)

title: oven-fried sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut crosswise into 3/8-inch slices.
Combine breadcrumbs and rosemary.
Dip each slice in milk and dredge in breadcrumb mixture.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet and coat with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in shredded carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onions. Combine stuffing mix and melted butter or oleo.

title: camping cabbage
directions: You will need tinfoil.

title: old-fashioned chicken main-dish soup
directions: In large pan, combine ingredients.
Bring to boil, simmer 10 minutes.

title: marinated baked fish
directions: In 12 x 7-inch baking dish combine all ingredients except fish.
Add fish; marinate 1 hour.
Cook tightly covered on 100% power (High) 5 to 7 minutes in microwave or until fish flakes with fork.
Garnish as desired.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Put Velveeta cheese (cut into cubes) and Pet milk in a crock-pot and let melt slowly.
Stir occasionally.
While cheese melts, brown sausage in skillet and drain grease.
Once cheese has melted, add sausage and about 1/3 of Ranch dressing mix to the cheese and stir.
Pour over nacho chips or Fritos and eat.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Mix in mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in mixture; roll in crumbs.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and spices together and stir in pumpkin.
Add Milnot and eggs.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then decrease heat to 350°.
Bake another 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is firm (when knife inserted in pie comes out clean).
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook with a little onion.
In broth, add chicken and celery soup.
Break off and add noodles.
Put chicken back into pot.

title: shrimp or crab mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese together until smooth and melted. Remove small amount of mixture and add gelatin to dissolve, then return to soup mixture.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients with a few dashes of Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and pour into oiled mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift
together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Blend
together
shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in the dry ingredients gradually.
Mix well and add pecans and dates.
Mix well.

title: mom's jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs with salt; add sugar and beat.
Add boiling water and beat.
Add flour mixture and beat.
Use beater entirely for this cake.
Bake in cookie sheet with sides at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Lay a towel out on counter.
Cover with powdered sugar. Lay cake out of pan onto towel.
Roll from narrow side.
When cake is cool, carefully unroll; spread with jelly, then roll back into a roll.
Slice with a serrated knife.

title: angels balls(christmas cookie)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large saucepan and cook 6 minutes, stirring continuously.
Add vanilla.
Stir in nuts and Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar. Store in tightly covered container.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix together jello and hot water and cool before adding rest of ingredients.
Mix all together and chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Cook on High for 10 minutes in microwave, stirring after the first 5 minutes.
No mess to clean up!!

title: southern chess pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to fill.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat sugar and butter until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, currants and nuts. Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or just until filling is set in center (shake pie gently; center should be firm).
Let cool on wire rack.
If desired, serve garnished with whipped cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: russell's pancakes
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Gradually add milk and egg.
Mix well.
Add shortening. Drop by spoonfuls on hot nonstick griddle and brown on both sides. Serve hot with fruit or syrup.

title: beef-oregano casserole
directions: Cook beef; save juice.
Cook noodles; add bouillon cubes to water and cook up most of liquid.
Do not drain.
In large bowl, combine beef cubes, soup, milk, onion flakes, oregano, pepper, salt and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Put in large buttered casserole. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Add a little milk if needed. Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes uncovered and bake 10 minutes more at 350°.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Place chicken skin side up in roasting pan. Slice 3 medium onions over chicken and pour sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste now and then.

title: grandma's chew bread
directions: Combine sugar and eggs in heavy saucepan; stir well and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring mixture well.
Spoon mixture into greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: toasted sesame sticks
directions: Cut bread, biscuit or bread dough into strips, 1/2 x 1/2 x 4-inches (remove crust from bread).
Spread thinly with butter. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until delicately brown.
Goes real well with any type soup.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Take 2 slices bread and butter one side of each.
Put one piece of the bread buttered side down onto a hot griddle.
Put a slice of cheese on top of bread and put the other piece of bread, buttered side up, on top of cheese.
Let bottom get light or golden brown.
Turn and do the same to other side.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, pepper, onions, water chestnuts and pineapple.
In a small bowl mix vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar. Mix into vegetables.
Marinate several hours.
Add chow mein noodles just before serving.

title: cottage cheese-jello salad
directions: Place cottage cheese in large bowl.
Pour in the Jell-I (dry). Add fruit cocktail.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: microwave fun snack mix
directions: In a small microwave-safe bowl, combine butter, chili powder, cumin and garlic powder.
Cover and microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds or until butter is melted.
In a 3-quart microwave-safe dish, combine crackers, pretzels and peanuts.
Add butter mixture and mix lightly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; toss to coat. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 7 to 8 minutes or until mixture begins to toast, carefully stirring every 2 minutes.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: sunshine stir-fry(low-fat)
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice for sauce.
cut chicken breasts into chunks.
In large skillet, stir-fry chicken with garlic, ginger (small amount of oil) and Butter Buds for 2 to 4 minutes; add pineapple, carrots and bell pepper.
Cover and steam 2 or 3 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in spaghetti or serve over rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together the first 6 ingredients.
Add the pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Meanwhile, toast hard rolls.

title: split pea soup
directions: Boil hard for 20 minutes then slowly until peas are soft. Strain through a colander or food mill.

title: antipasto on a stick
directions: Alternate any of the items on 6-inch skewers.
Sprinkle with Italian dressing.
Arrange on serving tray.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork, which has been dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: easy moussaka
directions: Peel eggplants; slice 1/2-inch thick.
Brown slices quickly in large, heavy skillet in 4 tablespoons butter (more as needed). Set aside.
Heat 4 tablespoons butter in same skillet.
Cook onions until lightly browned.
Add ground meat; cook for 10 minutes.
Combine tomato paste with wine, parsley, cinnamon, salt and pepper; stir into meat.
Simmer, stirring frequently, until all liquid has been absorbed.
Remove from heat.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until slightly browned and bubbly.
(This may be frozen and then thawed at room temperature the night before baking.)

title: grilled oysters
directions: Heat coals to medium hot.
Place grill 4-inches above coals or preheat broiler.
Wash shells well and dry.
(They can be used again.)
Replace oysters in shell halves.
If broiling, place on cookie sheet.
Combine butter and garlic and spoon over oysters. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Grill or broil until they begin to puff.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add this to egg and zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Spray pans with Pam.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.

title: western bean casserole
directions: Cut each bacon strip into 4 to 5 pieces and saute with onion and hamburger until meat is browned.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Turn all into a large casserole or baking pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening. Add sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each. Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed mixture. Bake in 10-inch pan at 325° for 80 minutes.

title: cheese crescent coffee cake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of jelly roll pan.
Take 1 tube off rolls and press together to cover bottom of pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture on top of crescent dough. Smooth it evenly.
Gently stretch second tube over top of mixture. Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and chill in refrigerator.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut and serve.

title: white chocolate bread pudding
directions: Instructions on making the dessert were not included.
Maybe the ingredients were free and if we asked for the instructions, there would have been a charge.
I don't know, but mixing must be comparable to other recipes of this kind.
It was served with a topping, but I'm not sure what kind, possibly a vanilla, custard or lemon sauce.
A liqueur flavor would make a good sauce too.

title: macaroon cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating.
Fold in nuts, cracker crumbs, coconut and vanilla.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: beef dip or spread
directions: Chop beef into small pieces.
Place in food processor or blender with all other ingredients.
Blend thoroughly and adjust mayonnaise and cream to achieve desired consistency.
Makes 1 1/2 cups spread.

title: 1864 lincoln cake(named after the then current president, abraham lincoln)
directions: Mix ingredients to form a batter.
Place in loaf pan. (Ingredients may be altered to suit family preferences, for instance, shredded carrots or nuts may be added or substituted for other items.)

title: cream cheese pie
directions: In medium sized bowl beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Add cherry pie filling to top before serving, if desired.

title: refrigerate roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl. Stir in potatoes, sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and 3 cups of the flour. Beat until smooth. Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up. Cover bowl tightly; refrigerate at least 8 hours but no longer than 5 days. Punch down dough. Divide into 4 equal parts. Use 1/4 of the dough for any dinner roll recipe.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid to directions on package adding more sugar if you wish.
Mix gelatin according to directions; add to Kool-Aid along with lemon juice.
Serve over ice cream in punch bowl.
Fresh strawberries are an attractive addition.
Serves 30 to 35.

title: lime alive beverage
directions: Mix ice cream with limeade concentrate. Gradually add milk and green food coloring.
Pour into glasses and garnish with lime slices.
Makes 2 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat together corn, eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Blend in milk a little at a time.
Pour in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix together oleo, nuts and flour and put into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Mix and beat for 2 minutes the milk and instant pudding.
Spread over layer of cheese mix.
Cover with rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate. Cut in squares to serve.

title: chocolate raspberry ribbon cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 350° oven in a jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Cool cake completely. Cut crosswise into thirds.
Spread 1/2 cup preserves on bottom layer to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Spread second layer with remaining preserves. Beat whipping cream and powdered sugar in chilled bowl until stiff.
Frost top and sides.
Decorate with chocolate chips or shaved Hershey bar. Refrigerate remaining cake.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Defrost broccoli and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush crackers and stir into broccoli with 1 stick melted butter. Slice cheese and place on top so that casserole is pretty much covered with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix and crushed pineapple with juice until pudding is mixed thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill.

title: mexican pot roast
directions: Sprinkle the
pot roast with salt and pepper.
In a Dutch oven, heat oil and brown roast on both sides.
Remove meat and add onion and garlic to drippings and cook over medium heat until onion is tender, not brown.
Add tomatoes, peppers, oregano and salt.
Heat to boiling and reduce heat to simmer.
Return meat to pot and add olives.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add beans last 30 minutes to one hour of cooking time.
If roast is very fat, cool some and remove fat and bone before adding beans.
Serve with rice and a salad. Serves 6 to 8.

title: tortoni cups
directions: Combine ingredients and freeze in 8 muffin cups in muffin pan.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Stir in coffee.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Blend together well.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonful on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: lime pie
directions: Separate eggs.
In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks until light colored and thick.
Gradually add the sugar and lime juice. Heat 5 minutes over simmering water, stirring often.
Set aside to cool.

title: party time texas chili dip
directions: Heat the chili, cheese and tomatoes until cheese melts.
Serve with corn chips.
You can add jalapenos, if you dare.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt stick of oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put shortening into flour.
Add milk.
Make dough and divide in half.
Roll out and put 1/2 in bottom of pan.
Put blueberries on first half of dough.
Put other half of dough on top of the blueberries.
Heat water and sugar, but do not boil.
Pour mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spiced beef
directions: *Florence used chuck; Roy Sayler, Dallas, Texas, used brisket.

title: walnut and zucchini stuffed chicken
directions: Mix cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and walnuts; set aside. Mix zucchini, onion and spinach in another bowl.
In skillet, melt butter and stir-fry zucchini mixture on medium-high heat until dry.
Remove pan from heat and stir in cheese mixture until thick.
Add cream and stir on low heat for 1 minute until creamy. Add lemon juice; taste and adjust seasonings.
Slide fingers under chicken skin and spread stuffing under skin on each breast.
Bake chicken, skin side up, in a lightly oiled baking dish for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Baste skin with pan juices and bake 10 minutes more until skin crisps.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Cream sugar and oil together, add eggs and pumpkin, beat well.
Add salt and spices and vinegar, then one cup flour.

title: fritti
directions: Place onion, grated cheese, beans and mushrooms in a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Whip milk, Bisquick and eggs with salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and top with sliced tomato. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Cook sugar and water to make a syrup.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cooked mixture slowly to egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla and cream of tartar.
Spread on cake.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Don't burn.
Cool.

title: chicken soupa
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add chilies and cook.
Then add soup and milk and bring to a boil.
Grease a large baking dish and line with buttered tortillas.
Then make a layer of chicken and a layer of cheese.
Pour milk mixture over this.
Cover with more buttered tortillas and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick autumn soup
directions: Brown the ground beef in soup pot until crumbly. Add onion. Cook 5 minutes longer. Stir in vegetables and next 5 seasonings and 2 cups hot water. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Stir in tomatoes and corn. Simmer 10 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: green bean and tomato salad
directions: Wash green beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Cook green beans covered in a small amount of boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain beans and set aside to cool. Combine beans and tomatoes in a shallow container.
Combine olive oil, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Pour over bean mixture; cover and chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: smokey country style ribs
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Sprinkle ribs with garlic powder and pepper.
Mix catsup, brown sugar (or substitute), chili sauce, vinegar, liquid smoke and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place ribs, meaty side up, on rack in roasting pan.
Brush with sauce.
Bake uncovered 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender, turning and brushing with sauce every 30 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces.
Heat remaining sauce to boiling.
Serve with ribs.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine everything but cream cheese in the top of a double boiler.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add cooked mixture, beating until well blended. Chill.
Serve with wedges of fresh fruit.

title: ham and egg pie
directions: Place hamburgers in bottom of baking dish.
Slice potatoes, carrots and onions.
Place over meat and cover closely with foil. Cook at 300° for an hour.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Boil until tender in small amount of water.
Saute meat, pepper, onion and celery.
Crumble cornbread, then add meat mixture, eggplant and soup.
Add salt and pepper. Mix all together.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the Dream Whip by package directions. Add the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix all together and put in graham cracker pie shell. Top with strawberries.

title: quiche onion tart
directions: Saute onions in hot butter until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in salt and cumin.

title: hurricane smoothie
directions: Pour all ingredients into a blender and whirl like a hurricane until smooth and thick. Tasty breakfast idea! Makes 3 cups or 3 to 4 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water; cook until tender.
Add ham, onion and butter.
Cook 15 minutes on medium heat.
Add milk.
Then when it's good and hot, drop rivels in slowly by spoonfuls.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix all ingredients well. Divide and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake pie for 40 more minutes.

title: swedish cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers into mixing bowl.
Slice onion; add to cucumbers.
Toss with vinegar, salt and sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, dill and parsley. Add to cucumbers and mix well.

title: mint tea punch
directions: Pour boiling water over mint sprigs and tea bags.
Steep 7 to 8 minutes.
Squeeze tea bags gently and remove.
Remove mint and discard.
Add sugar, orange and lemon juices.
Stir well until sugar is melted.
Add cold water.
Stir well.
Serve over crushed ice.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: trisha's favorite meal
directions: Saute garlic in oil until brown.
Stir in all ingredients, except spaghetti, break up tomatoes, heat until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 2 hours, stir frequently.
Cook spaghetti according to directions on package.

title: mama's one dish meal
directions: Brown ground beef; saute onion, celery and pepper in oleo. Mix with beef; add rice, water, tomatoes and chili powder.
Cover and cook on top of stove until rice is done.
(You may need more water.)
When done, add 1 can kidney beans.
Heat.
This can be put in casserole dish and topped with grated American cheese.

title: great fudge
directions: Butter a 10 x 6 x 1/2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in pudding and milk.
Bring to a full boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat in powdered sugar, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour in dish.
Chill.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: danish pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers. Cut in half and remove seeds. Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse in cold water and dry with paper towel or drain.
Boil cucumbers in vinegar mixture to a rolling boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: m & m's fudge-filled bars
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inch.
Mix oats, flour, nuts, brown sugar, baking soda and salt in a large bowl; stir in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 1/2 c. crumbly mixture.
Press remaining crumbly mixture into pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Heat shortening in 1-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in 1 cup of the candies; press candies with back of spoon until candies break into pieces.
Cook and stir until chocolate is melted (pieces of candy coating will remain); remove from heat, stir in milk.
Spread over baked layer to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Mix reserved crumbly mixture and remaining candies.
Sprinkle evenly over chocolate mixture; press lightly.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes; cool.
Cut into bars, about 2 1/4 x1 1/2 inches.
Makes approximately 50 bars.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles till tender. Rinse in cool water, drain. Melt butter and add ground beef. Brown and drain. Add salt, pepper and tomato sauce, simmer 5 minutes and remove from heat. In a separate bowl, combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and noodles. Alternate layers of meat mixture and noodle mixture in a casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans; cover in water and let soak overnight. In a pot, heat olive oil. Add onion, green onion, bell pepper and garlic. Saute over medium heat until vegetables are soft. Add the bay leaf, pepper, thyme, oregano and paprika. Drain the beans (discard water). Add the beans to the pot, along with 6 cups fresh water. Bring to a simmer; cover and cook until the beans are tender, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: tuna or shrimp wiggle
directions: Make a medium white sauce with shortening, flour and milk. Add shrimp and peas.
Season to taste.
Serve on crackers.

title: better than sex cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan bake cake according to directions. Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, cook pineapple juice and 3/4 cup sugar until it thickens.
Stir constantly, about 20 minutes.
When cake is done, punch cake with a fork; pour over pineapple evenly and cool.

title: nacho fondue
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir soup.
Stir in cheese and milk. Heat over low heat until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth and bubbling, stirring constantly.
Stir in salsa; remove from heat.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs, beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas; add nuts.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: mother's apple pie
directions: Mix cinnamon, sugar, flour and apples.
Place in crust.
Dot with butter.
Put on top crust and slit it.
Seal.
Brush water on top crust.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: million dollar pies
directions: Toast 1/2 cup coconut to put on top.
In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand, pineapple, 1 cup coconut, pecans and lemon and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts.
Garnish with 1/2 cup toasted coconut.
Chill 3 hours until set.
Refrigerate.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Lightly but thoroughly mix together all ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place in baking pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: aunt nell's famous cheese straws
directions: Mix oleo and grated cheese.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add slowly to cheese mixture.
Press with cookie press or pastry press to desired shape.
Aunt Nell likes two-inch straws that are about 3/4 of an inch wide.
Cook about 15 minutes at 350°.
Be sure to check them halfway during baking.
Enjoy!

title: chili chip casserole
directions: Brown ground beef until crumbly.
Add onion, chili seasoning mix, tomato paste and water.
Combine thoroughly.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Place 1/2 bag (about 2 cups) corn chips in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Spoon 1/2 chili meat mixture over corn chips. Place 1/2 can pinto beans over meat mixture, then place 1 can olives over beans.
Sprinkle with 1 cup grated cheese.
Repeat the meat, pinto beans and olive layers.
Arrange remaining corn chips over top and sprinkle with remaining cup grated cheese. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with salt added. Drain beef and transfer to large bowl.
Add potatoes, soup, sour cream, cheese and chopped onion; mix well.
Spread in baking dish. Bake 30 minutes.
Top with French-fried onions.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed in a large bowl.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 20 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook beans and onion in skillet.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and mustard.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in beans.
Pour into a bean pot or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: jamaican chicken
directions: Place pineapple slices in 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch dish.
Top with chicken breasts.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and coffee.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake until melted.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: *Add 1 teaspoon salt and one teaspoon soda if using plain flour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs, well beaten, then flour, salt, vanilla, syrup and pecans.
Put into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake in oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cucumber delight
directions: Combine sour cream, vinegar, sugar, garlic powder, dill weed and salt. Add cucumbers and onions. Toss all together to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: festive holiday bark
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Melt candy, stirring constantly, in medium saucepan over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat.
Spread mixture thinly on waxed paper. Let stand until set.
Break into pieces.
Makes 42 pieces.

title: tangy lemon pie
directions: Beat ingredients together until fluffy.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients 1 minute on high speed or until smooth.
Pour in pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mocha cheesecake(frozen)
directions: In small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
In buttered 9-inch spring-form pan, pat crumbs firmly on bottom and up sides of pan.
Chill.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; add condensed milk and chocolate syrup and beat.
In small bowl, dissolve coffee in water and add to condensed milk mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cover. Freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional chocolate crumbs.
Serve.
Freeze leftovers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water until soft.
Add sugar and cook for 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O and cook for 5 minutes.
Add Jell-O; let cool.
Add other ingredients and mix well, then chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spray a large sheet pan with Pam. Place crescent rolls whole on sheet pan. Form a crust. Press the seams together to close any cracks. Bake at 350° until lightly brown; let cool. Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, Ranch dressing mix and cream cheese and spread over the crust. Sprinkle over spread the remaining ingredients. Chill in the refrigerator for several hours before cutting into serving pieces.

title: apple nobby cake
directions: Mix all together.
Add apples.
Put in a greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gooey microwave brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in cocoa.
Beat in eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Pour into a round 8 to 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave on "bake" or 50 to 60% power for 5 to 10 minutes.
The center will look like a moon crater.
Let cool.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and milk together.
Layer in baking dish, half of chicken (cut in pieces), half of soup mixture and dry dressing. Repeat layers.
Top with chicken broth and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco party wings
directions: Combine taco seasoning, salt, meal and parsley flakes in plastic bag.
Shake wings in bag, a few at a time, until coated. Place in a single layer on greased shallow baking pans.
Bake in 350°
oven for 25 minutes.
Turn wings and bake 10 minutes more or until tender and brown.

title: honey garlic chicken
directions: Place chicken in medium bowl, add 1 cup vinegar and marinate at least 1 hour at room temperature.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Fill skillet half full with cooking oil.
Prepare muffin mix as directed, using egg and milk.
Slice tomatoes and dip each slice into muffin batter.
Cook each coated piece for 1 to 2 minutes in hot oil.
Let drain on paper towel covered plate.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Can also use batter for fried squash.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Let ice cream get soft enough to put half in each pie shell. Put in freezer to freeze again.
Slice when ready to make sundae.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a Pyrex bowl that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 30 minutes on 350°.
Makes 4 servings.
Count as 3 ounces protein or meat, 1 vegetable and 1 oil.
Half supplements for lunch or dinner.
tags: Hi-Energy Cream of Chicken Soup Supplements

title: strawberry bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and sugar; mix in oatmeal.
Cut in butter until mixture forms coarse crumbs.
Beat egg and milk.
Gradually add egg mixture to flour mixture, mixing until well blended.

title: pineapple bavarian mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and pineapple with juice.
Chill until thickened.
Stir to distribute fruit. Measure 1 3/4 cups and pour into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or 6-cup mold.
Chill 5 minutes.
Blend whipped topping into remaining jello mixture.
Carefully spoon onto mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold.
Serves 10 people or 5 cups.

title: chewy chocolate macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, stir together coconut and cocoa.
Stir in condensed milk and vanilla until well blended.

title: ma's doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix until well blended.
Chill about 1 hour, then take about half of dough at a time, roll on floured surface to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and fry in 375° deep fat for about 1 minute; turn once.
Remove with long-handled fork onto paper towels.
Makes about 3 dozen.
If you add 1 grated apple, doughnuts will be moist.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil eggs; set aside.
Drain pickles.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cool water. Mix everything together and let chill at least one hour.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large saucepan cook ground meat until browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except cabbage) and 5 cups water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf.
Add chopped cabbage and simmer another 1/2 hour.
Add more water if needed.
Serves 6.

title: strudel
directions: Mix together and chill in refrigerator for about 3 hours or longer.
Divide in 3 portions.
Take one out at a time so remainder keeps cool.
Place a clean cloth on table, sprinkle with flour and roll as thin as possible.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with crushed corn flakes or vanilla wafers.
Spread with your favorite filling and roll up.
Seal by pinching dough together. Place strudel carefully on well-greased baking pan.
Brush with melted oleo and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
Dough keeps well for several days.

title: white chocolate and macadamia nut cookies
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Beat well at medium with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool slightly on cookie sheet.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
(Mixture scorches easily.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: candied popcorn
directions: Boil 2 to 5 minutes over medium heat. Pour over 1 1/2 bags of microwavable popcorn; stir. Put on cookie sheet to cool.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown ground beef; put into a large saucepan.
Chop onion; add to ground beef.
Put in the jalapenos, diced.
Add kidney beans, tomato paste, water, salt and garlic.
Bring to a boil, then let simmer for about 1 hour.
Add more water when needed.
Eat with cornbread or crackers.
Dinner is complete.
Feeds about 10 people. If feeding more, double recipe.

title: fluffy pink salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: orange milkshake
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.

title: layered beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven layer ingredients in order.
Do not stir.
Do not mix.
Just layer.
Bake 5 hours at 250° with lid.
Do not open oven for 5 hours.
Yum! Yum!

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Saute butter and onions, add sliced mushrooms. Add chicken broth. Heat to boiling. Add flour and milk to thicken. Add 1/2 and 1/2 and can of soup. Heat through again.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Fix cake mix as directed on package.
Allow to cool completely.
Cream together cream cheese (softened) and vanilla pudding with only half the milk required in pudding directions. Spread this on top of cake.
Drain pineapple and spoon on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Chill!

title: hard candy
directions: Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
When candy thermometer reaches 300° take off stove.
Stir in flavoring and then coloring. Pour in thin strips over powdered sugar which is spread over a formica top.
Use enough powdered sugar so it won't stick to the table top.
Let cool a little, then start to break in small pieces.

title: parmesan salad
directions: Break broccoli flowerets into tiny bites; thinly slice stem portion.
Combine cauliflower, onions and 3/4 jar bacon bits. Toss with combined mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and sugar. Sprinkle with remaining bacon bits.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter or margarine in large shallow pan over low heat.
Stir in Worcestershire and seasoned salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix over low heat until all pieces are coated.
Heat for 45 minutes in oven, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread out on absorbent paper to cool.
Yield: 6 3/4 cups.

title: sherry paprika chicken
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in large, flat baking dish.
Pour a can of mushrooms over it. Sprinkle a lot of paprika and add sherry.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken with salt, onion and celery top with leaves in water enough to cover.
When done, take lid off and cool in broth. Remove bones and skin from chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces. Over this, pour a small amount of broth.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Put remaining broth in jar and leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: french toast casserole(serves 12)
directions: Lightly spray a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with nonfat cooking spray.
Arrange bread in bottom of baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a food processor or blender and process until all ingredients are blended.
Pour liquid mixture over bread; cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate one hour or overnight.

title: nettie's meatballs
directions: Boil frozen onions.
Make chopped meat into balls, seasoning meat to taste.
Add meat to pot of onions.
Add water only to cover meatballs.
Add whole cranberry sauce.
Add tomato sauce. Cook until done.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop jalapeno peppers, tomato and onion.
Put in bowl and serve.

title: cinnamon dip
directions: Combine ingredients and beat until smooth.
Store in covered container in the refrigerator.
Serve with fruit or cookies.

title: roundup chow
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger.
Add beans and heat, mixing in brown sugar, mustard and barbecue sauce (adjust amounts of these 3 ingredients to suit your individual taste).
Serve hot with or over biscuits or cornbread.
This dish is simple and filling; should feed 2 people, depending upon how much you eat!

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Combine noodles and all other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen.

title: creamy pea soup
directions: Rinse peas in cold water; set aside.
In a 6-quart Dutch oven, cook bacon; drain and dice.
In bacon fat, cook celery and onion until clear.
Add peas, water and everything but cream.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until peas are tender.
Stir.
Take out bay leaf.
Fill blender 3/4 full; blend until pureed.
Pour into large bowl; continue until done.
Return to same Dutch oven.
Add cream; cook until hot, 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir.
Serve with crumbled bacon and parsley on top.
Serves 12.

title: nutty cinnamon ring
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 of nuts in 9-inch ring mold.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit in melted oleo and then in sugar mixture.
Place 12 to 14 biscuits in mold.
Overlap slightly. Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Top with remaining coated biscuits, also remaining sugar mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn onto serving plate.
Let stand a few minutes.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Place sherbet in a punch bowl.
Gradually add chilled 7-Up until desired thickness is achieved.

title: favorite potato soup
directions: In saucepan, combine potatoes, carrots, onion, zucchini and water.
Simmer for about 15 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Do not drain water; set aside.

title: fancy chinese tuna salad
directions: Mix first seven ingredients and chill.
When ready to serve, stir in soy sauce blended with mayonnaise.
Serve on greens and garnish with olives, almonds and tomato.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil 1 minute.
Pour over 1/2 gallon popcorn.
Bake in low oven at 200° for 1 hour.

title: do-ahead herb-stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes early in the day.
When done, remove and cut 1 slice from long side of each potato.
Scoop inside of each potato (without breaking skin) into a large bowl.
Mash potatoes with the 3 tablespoons butter and enough cream to make light and fluffy; beat well.
Stir in rosemary, chives, parsley, sage, salt and pepper.
Pile potato mixture lightly into shells.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, reheat potatoes in a 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until browned and heated through.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: burger-noodle bake
directions: Combine meats and brown lightly in 12-inch skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Add soup, cheese, sugar and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let set.
Mix sugar and cold water.
Bring to boil.
Let cool.
When sugar and water mixture has cooled, add gelatin mixture, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Freeze in plastic containers.
Thaw approximately 3 hours and add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: oreo pudding and cream
directions: Crush cookies and mix well with melted butter (reserve 1/4 cup for topping).
Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese and beat in milk, adding milk in small amounts.
When mixture is smooth and foamy, add pudding mixes.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes until thick.
Spread pudding on cookie mixture.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle reserved cookies on top of Cool Whip; chill or serve immediately.

title: chocolate passion dessert
directions: Cut brownies into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer in 3-quart serving bowl 1/2 of the brownies,
1 cup strawberries, 1 sliced banana and 1 tub of topping.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate.
Serves 16.

title: billy's "rave" boneless pork loin
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients in a glass dish; add pork loin. Marinate 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally. Grill on low to medium coals for 45 minutes to 1 hour, turning every 10 to 15 minutes and basting each time with reserved marinade.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix shortening (oleo), sugar and eggs together.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients, then bananas. Add vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, peanut butter and brown sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients after sifting together.
Form into tiny balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, bell pepper and green onions in a bowl.
Chill overnight.
Drain and rinse kidney beans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Layer cheese on top.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator for 3 hours before serving.

title: mcintosh open-face sandwich
directions: Spread bread with mayonnaise, then mustard. Top with ham slices.
Core apples, but do not pare them.
Slice crosswise about 1/8-inch thick to make 18 slices.
Place 3 apple slices on each piece of bread.
Top each with 2 slices cheese.
Place on broiler pan and broil until cheese melts and browns slightly.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 open-face sandwiches.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook the onion with the squash.
Mix butter, eggs, onion, soup, and seasoning with cooked squash.
Crumble corn bread into mixture. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Pour into shallow baking dish or pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken-vegetable lo mein
directions: In medium bowl, combine 2 tablespoons water, 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Add chicken and toss until coated; set aside.
In small bowl, mix 1/2 cup water, remaining 2 tablespoons cornstarch, remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce and the sugar; set aside.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix together and make into a loaf.
Put in dish or pan.
Pour one can celery soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and asparagus
directions: Boil and bone chicken. Saute onions and mushrooms in butter. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until cheese melts.
In 9 x 13 casserole dish, layer asparagus and chicken.
Pour cheese mixture on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apricot jello mold
directions: Mix water and Jell-O.
Let set until lightly jells.
Add apricots and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in mold and let set in refrigerator.

title: chicken rotel #2
directions: Cook chicken breasts until well done.
Saute diced onion in 4 tablespoons of butter and 1/4 cup water.
Add diced chicken and Ro-Tel; cut cheese into small pieces.
Add slowly to mixer.
Boil noodles until tender; drain.
Put in large casserole dish.
Pour ingredients over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage roll
directions: Stir milk into biscuit mix; roll dough on floured surface until thin.
Spread dough with sausage and cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lazy tin can meal
directions: Dump all ingredients into casserole dish.
Mix and top with croutons or crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach pie
directions: This is a simple, delicious recipe and all you have to do is mix all the ingredients together.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cold zucchini and buttermilk soup
directions: Saute well.
Blend all and add buttermilk, salt and pepper. Chill and garnish with dill and parsley.

title: pluckets
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Add 1/3 cup sugar, butter and salt to scalded milk.
When cooled to lukewarm, add the dissolved yeast, eggs and just enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise until mixture doubles in bulk.
Knead down; let rise again.
Roll small balls of dough about the size of walnuts; dip them in melted butter.
Roll each ball in a mixture of 3/4 cup sugar, the ground nuts and the cinnamon.
Pile balls loosely in ungreased angel food cake pan; let rise again for about 30 minutes.
Bake for about 40 minutes at 400° and for 10 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: tomato pie
directions: Arrange tomato wedges in pie crusts so crusts are covered. Mix mayonnaise and Cheddar together.
Spread over wedges.
Salt and pepper, if desired.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts and is bubbly.
Serve with a meat dish or simply a salad.
Yields 2 pies.

title: cow chips
directions: Combine.
Drop by 2 1/2 tablespoons on greased cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chalupa
directions: Combine pork, dry beans (after overnight soaking), garlic, chili powder, cumin, oregano, chiles and salt in large kettle. Add water to cover. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer about 6 hours. Break up meat and cook, uncovered, until thick, about 45 minutes.

title: mostaccioli
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown sausage; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mostaccioli; set aside.
In a bowl, mix egg, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan or 3-quart casserole; spread 1/2 of the mostaccioli mixture.
Layer cheese mixture over all; top with remaining mostaccioli mixture.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Top with Romano or Parmesan cheese; bake 5 more minutes.
Garnish with basil, if desired.

title: date squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Turn into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.
Freezes well.

title: english-style scones(diabetic recipe)
directions: Beat 2 eggs, cream and vanilla.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter with 2 knives until coarse crumbs. Stir in dates/raisins.
Add egg mixture until moistened.
With floured hands, knead dough 4 times on lightly floured surface. Place dough on greased cookie sheet.
Pat into 8-inch circle. Gently score 3/4 way through into 6 wedges with sharp, wet knife. Beat 1 egg with 1 teaspoon water to brush over dough.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat water and butter; bring to a boil, then add flour.
Let batter cool.
This is a must.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Spread batter into well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass pan; put a little on sides with your spoon.
I pull it up from the bottom.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.

title: sweet-potato fritters
directions: Spread potatoes and onion on clean dish towel; roll up, twisting to get moisture from vegetables.
In bowl, whisk eggs, flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
In large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add vegetables to batter; mix.
Spoon mixture into skillet (1 heaping tablespoon).
Flatten slightly. Fry 4 minutes, turn and cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels; keep warm while frying others, adding oil if necessary. Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage meatballs(yields 40 small)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into 3/4 to 1-inch balls. Brown slowly in large skillet and drain.

title: quick orange cake
directions: Add hot butter to 1 cup sugar.
Add well beaten egg and orange juice.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat well.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in pineapple (10 minutes); stir in Cool Whip. Chill 1 hour.

title: skillet herb roasted chicken
directions: Combine flour, sage and thyme; mix together and put in a bowl or waxed paper or plastic sack for shake and bake.
Dip chicken in this mixture.
Put in skillet with hot margarine; brown on both sides.
Mix soup with water or milk; add to chicken.
Cover and simmer until done.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend broth into soup in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix in remaining ingredients but save 1/2 cup of the noodles.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle the remaining noodles crushed over the top.

title: hawaiian marshmallow pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with reserved liquid over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in pineapple and whipped topping.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.

title: sweet sour cabbage slaw(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Boil vinegar and oil until it comes to a boil; add sugar and remaining seasons.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour hot mixture over cabbage and onion.
Cover and chill overnight.
Keeps a long time in refrigerator.

title: peach barley casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish, arranging peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ivy's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake on hot griddle, making pancakes any size.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in
a	large skillet over medium to high heat. Add onions and	saute
until
translucent.
Stir in celery and green peppers.
Cook
until crisp and tender.
Add meat, rice, water chestnuts	and
almonds.	Heat
thoroughly,
stirring constantly.
Blend in egg mixture until well coated.
Continue cooking, stirring
frequently until golden brown.
Season with soy sauce to taste.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add 1 package taco seasoning.
Cool. Add lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, onion, green pepper and olives. Just before serving, add Doritos and dressing.
Toss and serve.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Remove and place slivered almonds on top.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in tight jar.
To serve, mix 3 teaspoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend at light speed in blender. Count to 10 slowly.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion, and mustard until creamy.
Drain shrimp and mix into cream cheese mixture with a fork, (mashing the shrimp as you mix).
Mix well and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, salt, pepper, sugar and flour.
Add beaten egg and margarine.
Drop by tablespoons in greased frypan. Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat white of eggs and salt until very stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar for stiff meringue.
Beat in vanilla and mix in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Put in oven and turn off heat.
Let cookies stay in oven for 8 to 10 hours.

title: banana boats
directions: Peel and slice bananas.
Put in individual serving bowls.
Top with marshmallows, chocolate chips and coconut.
Microwave until chips start to melt approximately 1 minute.
Let cool slightly.

title: homemade mac-n-cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and put in casserole dish.
Slice up cheese. Melt 4 tablespoons butter; add flour.
Stir; add milk and stir. Add cheese to mixture and stir frequently.
When melted, add to macaroni and mix.
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter and add bread crumbs; put on top of macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Mix in apple pie filling.
Fold in yellow cake mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: german's chocolate angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until foamy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition. Continue beating to very stiff peaks.
Fold in vanilla and nuts. Spoon into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan to form nest-like shell; build sides up 1/2-inch above edge of pan.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix together in jar with tight lid.
To use, put 1/3 cup mixture in cup and add boiling water.

title: meat and potato quiche
directions: In a 9-inch pie pan, stir together oil and potatoes.
Lightly salt.
Press evenly into pie crust shape.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or just until beginning to brown.
Remove from oven and layer on the cheese and meat.
In a bowl, beat together the milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over other ingredients. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Knife inserted 1-inch from edge should come out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: prune cake prune cake topping
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil.
Beat eggs and buttermilk. Add prunes.
Spray cake pan with Pam.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put 1/2 of bread cubes in bottom of pan.
Mix chicken, celery, onions, chestnuts, mayonnaise and salt and spread over bread cubes.
Then cover with remaining bread cubes.
Combine eggs and milk and pour over and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, cover with soup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: reverend painter's collard greens
directions: Serving Suggestion:
Serve with large skillet full of homemade cornbread.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk and chicken broth.
Stir in flour. Make gravy consistency.
Stir and boil about 15 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and cooked chicken pieces.
Mix all together and put in pie shell.
Put other pie shell on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Fold creamed
Crisco,
sugar
and eggs. Make a paste of cocoa and red coloring.
Add to mixture.	Mix salt and vanilla with buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to other mixture. Mix soda and
vinegar
together and pour into mixture. Do not beat this. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, pepper and garlic in butter for 2 to 3 minutes. Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Remove vegetables and shrimp from pan with slotted spoon and set aside.
Most of butter stays in pan, but if needed, add more to brown rice for a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth and spices and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Add the shrimp and vegetables to pan. Heat through and serve.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat until smooth.
Bake at 300° in 8 x 11-inch pan 35 to 40 minutes until still shakes a little in the center.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla, milk and pumpkin.
Blend in cinnamon and flour.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and spinach casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and spinach until tender and drain.
Put spinach and broccoli in a 2-quart flat baking dish.
Add soup, Cheddar cheese and sour cream that have been mixed together.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Sprinkle top with part of reserved nuts.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store in jar.
Use about 1 tablespoon per cup of tea, as desired.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Mix shortening and eggs in warm milk; add to yeast mixture.
Add flour and knead, just a little.
Let rise 1 hour.
Shape into muffin tins.
Let rise 1 hour more.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool at least 5 minutes before trying to remove from pans.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add garlic and onion; cook 5 to 7 minutes, until just tender.
Add broth and 3 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Add pasta and cook 5 minutes.
Add the last 4 ingredients and cook 7 to 8 minutes.

title: pear chow
directions: Grind or chop first four ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and boil for 20 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal while hot.

title: chocolate peanut butter sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in a saucepan.
Add butter, peanut butter and milk; heat to boiling.
Serve warm over cake in dish. Serves 8.

title: carrot puree with kalamata olives
directions: Cook carrots and garlic in salted water until tender; drain well.
Make carrots into a smooth mixture with a masher or stick blender until smooth while adding butter and broth.
Add olives and cook over low heat just until warm.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: apple crunch
directions: Dump the 2 cans of apple filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put brown sugar and sprinkle with cinnamon on top. Stir together. Put cake mix on top. Cut the 2 blocks of butter in chunks and spread on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all other ingredients together in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, milk and water.
Put all dry ingredients into sifter and add to batter; which will be thin but okay.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes.
Test. Bake in greased long cake pan and ice when cool with Fudge Icing.

title: pat's blackened flank steak
directions: Grind all ingredients, except steak in food processor or blender.
Coat both sides of flank steak with dry mixture.
(If cooking only one steak, use half the mixture and save the rest for future use.)
Coat a seasoned cast-iron skillet with olive oil; heat until smoking.
(You may want to do this outside
on a propane grill, as the smoke could set off a smoke alarm.)
Sear steak on both sides; meat will be black.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add in eggs and beat.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add to first mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from spoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: herb seasoned meat loaf
directions: Put in one large bowl; mix thoroughly beef, stuffing, seasoning, eggs, onion, ketchup and steak sauce.
Put in a 3-quart oblong, baking pan.
Then firmly shape meat mixture to pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour until your meat is no longer pink.
Pink meat optional.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients, (Except fruit). Place fruit on bottom of baking dish. Sweeten to taste. Spread dough on top. Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: one-pot chicken
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and saute onion and celery 3 to 4 minutes.
Add the chicken.
Increase heat and toss with vegetables 1 minute longer.
Add vermouth and allow to boil 1 minute.
Add broth, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil; cover. Reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Stir and return to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer another 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mincemeat bars
directions: Measure 2 cups oatmeal; add flour, soda and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Cut in shortening until mix is crumbly.
Divide into 2 parts.
Pack 1/2 firmly in bottom of oiled 8 x 11-inch baking pan.
Spread mincemeat evenly on top, then add remaining dough and pack firmly.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into 14 to 16 bars.

title: onion cheese chicken bake
directions: Melt butter and add salt and pepper. Roll chicken to coat. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Add mushrooms and bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with onion rings and then cheese. Cook about 5 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Place 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet.
Add the bread cubes and stir to coat.
Saute over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes or until the bread is lightly browned.
Add the tomatoes and garlic to the bread.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cook, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper; stir in basil and remove from heat.
Place tomato mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle the Parmesan cheese over top and drizzle with remaining oil.
Bake until bubbling, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour liquids over beans and let marinate overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in butter; stir in beef, garlic, flour, seasonings and mushrooms.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add undiluted soup. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, and salt thoroughly.
Mix in shortening only until mixture is crumbly. Add most of milk and stir to mix.
Add more milk as needed to make dough that is soft but not too sticky to knead or touch.
Roll into biscuits, place in pan, and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: serbian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add oil or shortening.
Add sugar, salt and gradually add flour until it forms a soft dough. Knead mixture until smooth and elastic; turn into lightly oiled bowl.
Cover and allow to rise 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down; form into 2 loaves, in bread pans or one large loaf and place in greased pans.
Place loaves in middle of preheated 400° oven and bake 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned.
Remove onto cooling rack.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Put on Waverly crackers or crackers of your choice.
Makes 3 cups.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Lightly brown venison and chopped onion in skillet.
Mix sour cream, mushrooms and hot cooked noodles together.
Add to meat and onion mixture.
Place in large casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese corn
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes or until it makes a soft ball.
Add the next 3 and mix well.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: ginger peach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ginger ale.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Fold in peaches.
I prefer to use the peach juice as part of the water measurement.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Marinate at least 12 hours.
Bake at 325° for 4 hours; wrap in foil or cover pan.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Place apples in a lightly greased 9-inch round cake pan. Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup walnuts; sprinkle over apples.
Sift together flour, remaining sugar, baking powder and salt.
