Combine egg, milk and butter; add to dry ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Pour over apple mixture.
Top with remaining nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.
Excellent topped with whipped cream.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt in small bowl.
Stir in 1/4 cup milk and egg yolks; set aside.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup sugar and 2 cups milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture reaches full boil, remove from heat.
Slowly stir 1 cup milk mixture into egg yolk mixture.
Return all to saucepan.
Bring to boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Let stand until cool.
Slice 2 bananas; arrange in bottom of pie shell.
Add filling.
Garnish with sweetened whipped cream.

title: spaghetti with fresh tomatoes and mozzarella
directions: Cook spaghetti to al dente stage; drain well.
Toss while hot with remaining ingredients.
Serve while still warm.
Serves 6.

title: southern hamburger casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion in large skillet on medium heat.
Drain fat and return to skillet.
Add mushrooms, green chilies and cream cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, paprika and cumin.
Split each biscuit in half.
Pat biscuits into baking pan that is lightly greased.
Spoon meat mixture into dough.
Combine cottage cheese and egg; mix well and spread over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and red pepper flakes, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla until smooth.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Glaze or garnish as desired.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Makes one 10-inch cake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut off tops of broccoli.
Discard stems.
Cut into bite size pieces and put into large bowl.
Add onion and bacon. Add 1 cup cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar in a small bowl until well blended.
Add to broccoli mixture and stir to coat.
Serve at once or chill.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Shake oil, vinegar, wine, soy sauce, sugar, mustard, curry powder, salt and pepper until blended.
Toss with spinach; add bacon and eggs.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake, fix pudding mix by directions on mix.
Bread 1/2 of cake into bowl; pour 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Add pineapple chunks, coconut, nuts, banana slices and cherry pie filling over cake pieces.
Repeat again.

title: homemade snow and honey
directions: If you have an ice crusher, crush the ice cubes to a powdery snow.
By hand, put the ice in 2 or 3 plastic bags and cover with a double fold of foil.
Hammer until the ice is a powdery snow. Pour the warm honey over the snow and eat.

title: one-pot meal
directions: Brown meat in a skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add layers of vegetables in order.
Top with cut up tomatoes.
Add juice and water.
When potatoes and cabbage are tender, it is ready to serve.
Serve with cornbread.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Heat soup to melt cheese.
Mix jello with hot water; mix and cool.
Add to first mixture.
Fold in celery, pepper, onions and shrimp.

title: church window candy
directions: Melt oleo with chocolate chips over hot water.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Sprinkle coconut on 2 lengths of foil (12 to 15-inches long).
Spoon on mixture to form in roll. Refrigerate.
When cool and hard, slice.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix eggs, cheese, hamburg, salt and pepper together.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on box.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan layer of sauce, macaroni and filling; one or two layers regarding height of pan.
On top of last layer, put on grated or shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine beans and all other ingredients together except bacon. Put into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Cover layers with mayonnaise. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let this set overnight and toss just before serving.

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix chopped onion, parsley flakes, salt, paprika, egg, cornflake or bread crumbs and celery salt.
If too dry after adding crumbs, add another egg and if too wet, add more crumbs.
Add to ground beef and form into patties.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Cut ham and cheese in small pieces about the size of a roll.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour in 8-inch pie crust.
Bake at 450° then 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until knife comes out clean. Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate .7 g, protein 2 g, fat 1 g, calories 37.
One serving = 1 fruit exchange, 1/2 meat medium fat exchange.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in large pot until almost done.
Mix evaporated milk, 1 can of water and Cheez Whiz.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Add to potatoes and onions; salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 5 bean salad
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Saute celery and onions and add to sausage, cut in slices.
Add cans of beans and mix in rest of ingredients.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add a few strips of bacon.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or more at 350°.

title: old-fashioned corn bread(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a 12-inch iron skillet, which has been sprayed with a nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Soak bread with these ingredients for 15 minutes.
Stir lightly with fork.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place in baking dish in pan of hot water (1-inch deep).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm with milk or cream.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small frying pan, fry bacon until clear.
Add the margarine and all other ingredients except the shrimp.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place the shrimp in a open baking dish and pour sauce over top.
Stir once to coat all shrimp.
Bake in an uncovered dish for 20 minutes, stirring twice during baking. Serve hot.
You can peel shrimp after cooking but not before cooking or eat with peels on except the tails!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Can use Cheddar cheese soup or other favorite instead of mushroom and chicken soup.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix the sugar and cinnamon together and toss with biscuit pieces in plastic bag.
Place in a Bundt pan. Melt together the oleo and brown sugar. Add raisins to melted mixture.
Pour over rolls. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: beef barley
directions: In dutch oven, cook Beef in Olive Oil until no red shows. Add the finely chopped Onion; cooking for about 15 minutes. Add Water, Bouillon and Garlic Powder; bringing to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer (medium-low).

title: homemade waffles
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until it forms a foam.
Mix dry ingredients; add egg yolks, milk and oil.
Add egg whites gradually.
Mix only until blended.
Pour 1 1/4 cups on preheated waffle griddle.

title: sweet and sour shell salad
directions: Cook pasta shells as directed.
Mix all the ingredients together until well blended.
Pour over warm shells, tossing lightly.
Refrigerate until cool, but best if made the day ahead. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain and set aside. Saute onion in oleo.
Stir in broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and soup. Mix well.
Pour into a casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef tacos
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add beef and brown. Add onion and garlic. Continue cooking until onion is tender. Mix in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Heat, stirring occasionally. Spoon beef mixture into taco shells.
Top with cheese and lettuce.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift dry ingredients mixing well.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together to your taste.

title: chocolate covered marshmallows
directions: You will also need 40 toothpicks.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast, shortening and sugar in water. Stir in 4 cups flour, salt and egg. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a stiff dough. Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.

Cover and allow to rise in warm place, punching down every 10 minutes for 1 hour, then allow to rise for 1 additional hour or doubled. Punch down; let rest 10 minutes. Divide into 2 loaves. Place on greased cookie sheets and slash tops 3 times. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or golden brown.
Cool on wire rack. Brush with melted butter.

title: joyce's plum duff
directions: Sift flour and salt into a basin.
Add breadcrumbs, suet, currants and grated lemon rind; mix well.
Add milk to mix to smooth dropping consistency.
Spoon into buttered 1 1/2-pint bowl. Cover with buttered paper and tie securely, folding a pleat to allow pudding to rise.
Steam gently for 2 hours.
Serve hot with a custard sauce.

title: smothered pork chop
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops and season to your taste.
Drain well.
In crock-pot on medium, add pork chops and soup.
Cook until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: polish chili
directions: Brown the ground chuck with onion and chili powder in an 8-quart pot over low heat, stirring as needed to break up the chunks.
Cook until the onions are tender.
Add salt, brown sugar, beans and puree.
Cook 15 minutes.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and serve with a side of oyster crackers.

title: surprise filled cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
Mix well and set aside. Cream butter and sugar very well.
Add egg and vanilla and beat on medium speed until smooth.
Add flour mixture and blend at low speed until thoroughly combined.
Dough will be firm.
Roll tablespoons of dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet one-inch apart.
Using small end of melon baller, scoop out the center of the dough balls.
Do not scoop all the way through the cookies.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of jam in the center of each dough ball.
Bake at 300° for 22 to 24 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and brown in
skillet.
(Place
a
little
shortening in skillet.) Drain off liquid
and pour barbecue sauce over meat; simmer for 20 minutes. If desired meat may be transferred to a casserole dish after browning and
baked in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: good morning muffins
directions: Spray 10 muffin cups with nonstick spray.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, bran, baking powder, cinnamon and allspice. In small bowl, combine orange peel, juice, egg white, oil and honey.
Add to flour mixture; stir.
Add carrots.
Spoon into muffin cups, 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove and let cool.

title: country ham and potatoes
directions: In a large heavy skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat. Brown ham on both sides.
Move ham to one side of the skillet; brown potatoes in the drippings.
Sprinkle potatoes with parsley. Yields 6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large pan, cook beef with onions until tender.
Add broth, mushroom soup and water.
Cover and heat to boiling (stir often). Reduce heat to low.
Add noodles and sour cream.
Simmer about 10 to 15 minutes until noodles are tender.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Add onions, potatoes and tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly until potatoes are done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain chunk fruit and drain pineapple. Save juice.
Mix pudding mix with juice and Tang.
Add fruit.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal raisin spice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and baking soda; mix well.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in oats and raisins. Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: fried apples
directions: Rinse and peel apples.
Cut into wedges.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Add apples, cinnamon, sugar and vanilla extract. Cook on low.
Simmer approximately 20 to 25 minutes until apples are soft and crispy (not mushy).
Sprinkle cinnamon over top of fried apples.

title: crab meat casserole supreme
directions: Make sauce with butter, flour, milk and Worcestershire. Combine remaining ingredients, except crumbs, cheese and paprika. Add sauce to mixture.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: clara's cookies
directions: Beat together the egg yolks, vanilla, salt and soda.
Cream in the sugar and oleo.
Add the Crisco oil and flour.
Roll in balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: grandma raszman's mayonnaise-chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together until blended and bake in two round tins or 9 x 13-inch pan or whatever.
Bake at 325° in glass pan or 350° in metal pan.
Bake until done.

title: easy pot pie
directions: Saute celery, onion, thyme and pepper in margarine.
Mix soups and milk; add to meat and vegetable mixture.
Top with pie crust (from frozen section).

title: crackled crescents
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together flour and baking powder.
Set aside.

title: shrimp supreme
directions: Cut shrimp in half lengthwise.
Combine next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add shrimp and toss gently to coat.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Heat oil in a large skillet; add shrimp.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 3 to 5 minutes (until shrimp turn pink).
Remove shrimp and set aside.
Drain drippings, reserving 2 tablespoons in skillet.
Add onion, chopped red pepper and garlic to skillet. Saute until tender.
Add zucchini and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in shrimp, cooked rice and cashews (optional); cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 servings.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Place margarine in a saucepan with the water and bring to a boil.
Combine eggs and buttermilk to margarine, then pour into flour mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple bean bake
directions: Fry bacon and onion together until lightly browned.
Drain off fat.
Add cut up franks and pineapple chunks.
Cook together for a few minutes.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Split shrimp and season with salt, pepper and cayenne (be careful with the cayenne!); set aside.
Melt margarine and add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook slowly until onion is wilted.
Add shrimp and let simmer for 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add mixture.
Cook another 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: horry county chicken bog
directions: Place cut up chicken, ham hock, salt, pepper and onion in large pot with 5 1/2 cups of water.
Cook until well done.
Drain chicken broth; set aside.
Remove bones from chicken and ham; cut meat in bite size pieces and put back in pot.
Add smoked sausage. Add 5 cups of chicken broth from broth that has been set aside. If you have less than 5 cups, add water to equal 5 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Taste; add extra salt, if needed.
Add 2 cups of rice and stir.
Bring to a second boil.
Cover pot tightly; turn burner to low and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with cole slaw, pickles, bread and iced tea.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: broiled ham steak with honey mustard sauce
directions: Let ham soak in milk, turning once, 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Pat dry.
Whisk remaining ingredients.
Brush ham lightly with sauce.
Broil under preheated broiler (1-inch from heat), 4 to 8 minutes until top lightly browned.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine meat, pepper, onion and chili powder; cook until meat is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving cheese and Doritos.
In a greased 9 x 12 x 3-inch pan, place a layer of Doritos, meat and cheese, ending with meat mixture on top.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in a saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring, until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk; set aside.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Gradually stir in chocolate mixture, using a wire whisk.
Pour into pastry shells; sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Pie may appear soft but will firm after cooling.
Let cool for 4 hours.

title: fried soft shell crabs
directions: Remove the soft feelers or "dead man" under each side of the shell.
Remove eyes, mouth and sandbag under mouth.
Wash crabs well in cold water and dry on paper towel.
Mix milk and egg; season with salt and pepper.
Soak crabs in this mixture for one hour.
Roll in flour and fry in deep fat fryer for 20 minutes or until reddish brown.
Garnish with lemon slices and chopped parsley.
Serve with Tartar Sauce.
Serves 6.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Soak cabbage, green pepper and pimento in the water and salt. Leave for 1/2 hour. Bring to boil sugar, vinegar, water and mustard seed to make a syrup; cool. Drain cabbage; add celery and combine with syrup. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving. Keeps in refrigerator for 2 weeks or can be frozen.

title: perfect fluffy rice for fussy people
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Measure the rice into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Watch it!

title: corn bread(no sugar!)
directions: Measure flour and sift baking soda, salt and baking powder. Mix with corn meal.
Combine oil, honey and eggs.
Add buttermilk, mixing well, and combine with dry ingredients.
Beat only until smooth.
Fill well oiled 8 x 8-inch shallow pan 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: thomas's chili
directions: Mix tomato juice and puree in a large kettle. Add all of the spices. Mix and heat to almost a boil. Brown hamburger in skillet. Drain off grease. Add to kettle. In the skillet, cook onion half done. Drain. Add to kettle. Bring to a simmer. Add kidney beans. Cook spaghetti. Add to kettle; turn off heat. Let set for 1/2 hour.

title: green rice(broccoli rice)
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix well and pour in casserole dish and grate American cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast banana split
directions: In each banana split bowl, place half a banana split lengthwise.
Cover with half an apple, diced.
Wash and drain berries.
Top with one-half cup yogurt, then 1 tablespoon wheat germ.
Place a kiwi slice on top.
Serves 4.

title: owl face cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and peanut butter; mix thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in oats.
Divide dough in half to form a roll 8 inches long.
Add the melted semi-sweet chocolate to 1/2 of dough.
Roll out chocolate dough on wax paper to form an 8-inch square.
Place plain 8-inch roll on chocolate 8-inch square.
Wrap chocolate dough around plain.
Pinch seams together.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill at least 1 hour.
If dough is refrigerated several hours, allow to stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan. Add sugar and cocoa. Stir well and add eggs. Stir mixture. Do not beat. Add milk and vanilla. Pour into pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until crust is brown. Makes 1 pie.

title: italian baked fish
directions: Melt butter and add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip fish fillets in lemon butter sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste. Roll in bread crumbs and place in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes, basting once with lemon butter during cooking.
Do not overcook!

title: good
directions: Pour mushroom soup over the browned ground beef. Put frozen Tater Tots into beef and soup. Cook 30 minutes, until Tots are tender. Place cheese slices last 15 minutes of baking.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: In a large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour, walnuts, milk and vanilla extract.
Beat ingredients until well mixed.

title: pumpkin bars and frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 17 x 11 x 3/4-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 22 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Partially cool, then top with frosting.

title: chocolate icing
directions: If too firm, add 1 to 2 tablespoons hot water to soften.

title: miniature christmas fruit cakes
directions: In a saucepan, combine molasses, water and vanilla; Add raisins and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit; cool.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in fruit mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon into paper lined muffin cups, filling almost to
the top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: instant portuguese bean soup
directions: Boil
and
simmer
vegetable soup, water and Portuguese sausage
in a medium size pot.
Add kidney beans and macaroni. Serves 4 persons.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Soak raisins in boiling water until plump; stir.
Let cool.

title: diet apple pie
directions: Combine spices, margarine and cornstarch in bowl.
Set aside. Put apple juice in saucepan and bring to boil.
Add small amount of spice mixture until all blends.
Add Equal and mix well.
Put apples in pie crust.
Pour mixture over apples and cover with a crust.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 370° and cook for 30 minutes.

title: cindy's simple chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour and cocoa together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add mushrooms and saute until tender. Blend in flour and add chicken broth.
Heat until mixture comes to a boil, then cook gently for 5 minutes, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add seasonings and milk and stir over low heat a few minutes more.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with parsley.

title: dream bars
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in an 11 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9-inch fluted tube pan.
In mixer bowl, beat all ingredients, except confectioners sugar and lemon juice, 3 minutes. Pour into pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove cake from pan.
Cool.
Mix confectioners sugar and lemon juice. Drizzle over cake. Makes 12 servings.

title: delightful fruit salad(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a large bowl blend the fruit cocktail, pineapple, strawberries, mandarin oranges, banana and cottage cheese together.
Place into 6 individual dessert dishes.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Top each dish with light Cool Whip and serve.

title: western meal in one
directions: Brown beef in vegetable oil with garlic.
Add the onion and green pepper; cook until onion is transparent.
Drain off fat.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine the meat mixture, salt, chili powder, beans, tomatoes and rice.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese and olives; bake for 15 minutes more.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Use fingers.
Pinch off marble-size pieces and put on baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen.
Take out to thaw and serve.
Not necessary to reheat, but is an added touch.
Makes 40.

title: caramel pie(real good)
directions: Press into a 9-inch pie pan and chill.

title: cheddar scallion soda bread
directions: *Or add 1 1/2 teaspoons vinegar to 1/2 cup milk and let stand for a few minutes.

title: cocktail dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Crush crackers.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar.
Fold in nuts and crackers. Spread in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Beat the cream cheese.
Add whipped topping and fruit.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Cover; refrigerate or freeze.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute pepper, onion, mushrooms and pimiento in oleo until soft.
Melt together Velveeta, mushroom soup, chicken soup, tomatoes and 1 cup chicken broth.
Mix altogether.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbling.

title: french coconut
directions: Mix in order and cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello with hot water, add sugar, stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
15 to 20 minutes later add remaining ingredients.

title: whole wheat bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; stir well. Pour hot water over sugar and salt; stir until dissolved. Cool. Add softened yeast, shortening, molasses and whole wheat flour, beating until smooth. Add remaining flour

and work it in well with the hands. Turn onto floured pastry cloth and knead until smooth and elastic. Place dough in a greased bowl. Grease surface of dough. Cover and let rise until double in bulk (about 2 hours). Divide into 2 parts. Shape into loaves and place in greased loaf pans, about 8 x 4 x 3-inches. Cover and let rise about 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix cake mix and Cool Whip until blended.
Mixture will be thick.
Make into balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, no longer.

title: ashleigh's sweet toast
directions: Spread margarine on bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake at 400° until edges start to brown.
Watch closely. Yummy!!

title: hobo bread
directions: Soak raisins in boiling water with soda.
Stir and cover; let stand overnight.
Next day, add egg, sugar, vegetable oil, salt and flour (1 cup at a time), mixing well.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Melt butter and Wesson oil.
Saute celery, onion, green onion and bell pepper.
Add in cream of mushroom and chicken soups.
Add cheese.
Let simmer on low until mixture is all smooth.
Add small amount of chicken broth, if needed, for smoothness.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth, then drain.
Add soup mixture and chicken to spaghetti; season to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until casserole bubbles and cheese melts on top.

title: poor man's cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, butter and 1/3 cup sugar.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crumb mixture, reserving a few crumbs for topping.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray nonstick coating in 9 1/2 x 13 casserole. Melt butter on stovetop, then add cheese and sour cream and stir until melted. Add soups, broth and onions, mixing well. Put potatoes into casserole, then soup mixture and stir well. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Remove and top with crushed corn flakes that have been mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Bake, uncovered, for another 30 to 45 minutes.

title: betty ford's chicken salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and rice (cooked according to package directions) and mix well.
Pour chicken broth and vinegar over the mixture; mix and chill overnight.
Just before serving, add diced celery.

title: baked mustard chicken
directions: Brush chicken with mustard and sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Place
in
a
x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine butter, lemon juice
and water and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at	350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake another 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in milk and eggs.
Stir in salt, spices, flour, soda, oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop batter by tablespoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in Wispride crock.
Bake at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Makes 2 layers, each layer made of beef and sauce, noodles, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Use a 7 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If 1 1/2 cups water is added to sauce and hamburger, you will need a larger pan.

title: january 5th chili(crock-pot)
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil. Season with spices, salt and pepper. Add tomato paste and enchilada sauce. Stir in flour. Place in crock-pot.
Add garlic and beer.
Cook on high for 1 hour.
Reduce temperature to low and cook until done, about 4 to 5 hours. Check at 2 to 3 hours and add additional liquid (beer, water or beef bouillon).

title: lemon herb fish fillets
directions: Melt margarine in cup on Medium-high (70%) in microwave for 1 minute.
Add lemon juice, garlic salt, parsley and dill weed.
Pat fillets with paper towel to remove excess moisture.
Arrange in dish with thickest part of fillets toward outside of dish.
Pour margarine mixture over fillets.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes when touched with fork.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: covered bridge potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender; peel and dice.
Mince onions, dice carrot and celery.
Chop olives; slice hard-cooked eggs.
Combine potatoes, onions, carrots, celery, olives and sliced eggs; set aside.
Dice bacon; fry until crisp.
Stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Combine sugar, eggs, mustard, 1 cup water, vinegar, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add to flour paste.
Place over low heat; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over potato mixture; mix lightly.
Let stand in cold place for several hours.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: yogurt soup(spaas)
directions: Saute the barley and onion in butter.
Mix together the eggs, chicken broth, yogurt and flour; add to saute.
To this, add the remaining spices.
Cook until piping hot; don't let it curdle. Finally, add mint and the juice of 1 lemon.
Best chilled, but also good hot.
Serves 6.

title: coconut surprises
directions: Whip cream cheese with spoon until light and fluffy.
Add orange rind, lemon rind, walnuts and sweetener; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in moist unsweetened coconut.
Chill.

title: baked tuna balls
directions: Combine tuna, egg, bread crumbs, mayonnaise, onion, parsley, almonds, mustard and seasoning.
Mix well.
Shape into 40 balls. Roll in cornflakes.
Dip in butter (melted).
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Serve on cocktail toothpicks.

title: grammer's pesto sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor or if you don't have food processor, use tender ends of basil and mince.
Cut off parsley stems and chop leaves.
Peel and chop garlic.

title: beef macaroni superb
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water according to package directions.
Brown beef; add onion and pepper.
Simmer a few minutes.
Add tomato puree, water, mushroom soup, cooked macaroni, salt and cheese to casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients; add to zucchini mixture and mix well.
Pour into two greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: taco meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in baking dish and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown. Serve with toothpicks.
Makes 35 to 40 meatballs.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients until crumbly.
Place half of this mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour with blueberries and pack into pie shell.
Sprinkle remainder of mixture on top.
Mix 1 egg and 3 tablespoons milk and pour over pie.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Add egg, buttermilk and 3 tablespoons oil, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour remaining 1 tablespoon oil into 8-inch cast-iron skillet and place in a 425° oven for 5 minutes. Remove from oven. Spoon batter into skillet. Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.
The cookies will look unbrowned.
Do not bake any longer.

title: ham hocks and black-eyed peas
directions: Place dry peas in a 6 quart kettle or Dutch oven and add 12 cups water.
Soak as directed.
Don't drain.
Stir in ham hocks, onion, celery, bay leaf, salt and cayenne pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until ham hocks are tender and peas are done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place rice on the bottom. Layer broccoli next, then chicken.
In medium bowl combine soup, milk, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over layered ingredients.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown the beef in the shortening.
Add the onion and celery and cook 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Place half in a casserole dish and cover with half the cabbage.
Add the remaining meat and cabbage.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and flour, a little at a time.
Add flavoring and fold in chips.
Grease pan.
Pour in batter and cook in cold oven for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: bible cake
directions: Follow up with the directions of Solomon for bringing up a child.
Proverbs 23:14.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time and blend well after each addition.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour into pastry shell and bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake 25 minutes longer or until firm.

title: date pudding
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Mix dates and nuts.
Pour water over soda, dates and nuts.
Let cool.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, and vanilla and mix all ingredients together well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in oiled and floured pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan. Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Prepare cake mix.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together; add powdered sugar and mix well.
Pour mixture over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Cut into squares and serve.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: orange date cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Bake in sheath pan or 2 layers for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dewberries in cobbler crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in the oven in 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole, but do not let it brown.
Mix sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour into casserole over butter. Add berries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not stir at any time.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in small, oblong pan.
Pour peaches in pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over peaches; bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix last 5 ingredinets on the stove and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon soda; mix well.
Pour over popcorn and stir constantly until mixed.
Place in 250° oven and stir every 15 minutes for one hour.
Pour out of pan onto paper or waxed paper or it will stick in pan.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, unsweetened chocolate and 1 1/2 cups chocolate morsels in a large heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until butter and chocolate are melted; let cool.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Combine milk and crumbs.
Add ground meats, onion, sugar, salt and egg.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water and add to meat mixture; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 24 meatballs in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then pour off drippings. Spread soup over meatballs and continue to bake for around 45 minutes.

title: spicy vegetable soup(2 points- weight watchers)
directions: Mix all ingredients and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: fruit and vegetable salad
directions: Mix well and chill. Enjoy!

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise and cream cheese together in a mixing bowl; combine with diced orange sections, diced peaches, pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Whip cream and fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into mold or Pyrex dish and place in freezer for 3 hours or until frozen.
Unmold and serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and use cookie cutter to cut out cookies.
Then decorate with sprinkles or colored sugar.
Then bake in 350° oven for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil the chicken.
Remove from bone.
Heat the cheese.
Mix the chicken and cheese together.
Put the chips in a casserole dish.
Put the chicken and cheese in the casserole, then more chips.
Heat in oven at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and milk in saucepan; heat until bubbly. Set aside.
Melt margarine; mix with crumbled up corn flakes (crumble by hand).
Place corn flakes in bottom of casserole pan. Drain cabbage; spread over corn flakes, then pour soup mixture over cabbage.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade pork sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Make into patties and freeze until needed, if desired.

title: frosted raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; stir until smooth.
Add pineapple and spoon in lightly greased dish. Chill until firm.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix, let stand for 24 hours and drain.
Ready to serve.

title: beef and cabbage quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix corned beef hash, flour and 2 eggs thoroughly.
Press mixture firmly and evenly against bottom and sides to within 1 inch of top of ungreased baking dish (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch).
Bake meat crust 25 minutes.
Remove meat crust from oven; drain.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Store overnight in refrigerator before serving.
